7ccc8165-98cc-4fdb-a370-a71a4563dc31	content	<h1>Hey Friends</h1><div>Thanks for following along.  Or checking in sometime later in the future.  Or hey future Truman or Carrie reminiscing about what will hopefully be beautiful and fun trip.  Or if this is an artifact that's discovered in some apocalypse future, well, I hope you're alright and can lay your hands on some bottle caps or whatever is the currency du jour.<br><br>What will follow here is a brief accounting of our trip out west to get married in Yosemite.  Brief because I'm typing this after driving all day, and because my laptop's dumb butterfly keyboard keeps sticking my "T"s, and because I have the utmost care for my dear readers' time and attention.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jOWYyMjM5NS0yMzhmLTQwZjQtODMxZC05ZmUzM2E1ZDlhZmQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--74290b3f620ad147af98acb9506838abad47ef8f" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqT1dZeU1qTTVOUzB5TXpobUxUUXdaalF0T0RNeFpDMDVabVV6TTJFMVpEbGhabVFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--a6aadc8fffcc05923ebded863efd29577481d1b0/IMG_2599.jpg" filename="IMG_2599.jpg" filesize="152732" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="Hey I can add pictures to these things.  Pretty neat!"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>Packing</h1><div>We spent some time packing up over the last week or so.  Mostly throwing camping things in a bin, figuring out how to transport all of our costco peanut m&amp;ms, and wrangling all of the generous presents that folks sent (thank you so much, generally -- and a much more personal thanks forthcoming after we return home).<br><br>We also put some Nutzo in squeeze pouches, and worked through a long packing list, and tried not to check the Yosemite air quality index too often.  Carrie's mom came to visit the last weekend before we left and brought a helpful guide to writing vows.  It recommends several times to get started a few months in advance but, uh, oh well.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84ZGZmMmY2Yi0yMWI3LTRjMWEtOGZhZi0xYWYwODlkNmNmZWQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--bd02e063324b4c27d6ca8aa005b3d26b85ce57bd" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0WkdabU1tWTJZaTB5TVdJM0xUUmpNV0V0T0daaFppMHhZV1l3T0Rsa05tTm1aV1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--4673349b44aa5d9983b89e9402ebd8ef33113ae8/IMG_2603.jpg" filename="IMG_2603.jpg" filesize="117410" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="This will be us in Death Valley, with hopefully the same number of scorpions."></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jNmFhNjM1Yi01YjhkLTRhNjYtYjQyZS01NjBlN2EzZmEzMjc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--6a66a794a276ea17c110a76ca79c7981f59d9bfc" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqTm1GaE5qTTFZaTAxWWpoa0xUUmhOall0WWpReVpTMDFOakJsTjJFelptRXpNamNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--02a11ad31d421e537a9846d7a71aa34db47d42e6/IMG_2608.jpg" filename="IMG_2608.jpg" filesize="115164" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Catballs is not joining us, but is under the care of our wonderful downstairs neighbor, Michael."></action-text-attachment><br><br>We're really hoping to be able to snag either a backcountry permit, or an unclaimed reservation at Phantom Ranch at the bottom of the grand canyon.  Who knows if that will happen, but we decided to prepare some backpacking meals just in case we're able to hike down.  Carrie found what look to be <a href="https://www.theyummylife.com/Backpacking_Food">some great recipes</a>, which we sort of followed.  We're hoping to spend two nights down there because the hiking part seems pretty difficult and a little intimidating.<br><br> <action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iMzExMzIwMi02MTkxLTQ0NTctOTQzNC1jMWVmOGYyNTIzMDI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--510bc222261786be829ba30766822ee67ff469ed" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpTXpFeE16SXdNaTAyTVRreExUUTBOVGN0T1RRek5DMWpNV1ZtT0dZeU5USXpNRElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--645788c6a512c7477383f22d222f174c484492b9/IMG_2614.jpg" filename="IMG_2614.jpg" filesize="124269" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="&quot;Future Essentials&quot; speaks of a grim imagining of what the future may hold.  We'll let you know how it tastes in the more immediate future, later."></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>Setting Out</h1><div>We set out this morning at eight -- having planned for seven, only dropping an hour is a pretty big win.  Our first day will bring us to Bristow, Oklahoma (we originally planned for Oklahoma City, but decided to cut an hour) by way of St. Louis.  Expect some breathtaking photography of the Arch later on.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9kZTA1MGY3Ny1iNzhmLTRiOTAtYWM5OS1kMDgxYmUxM2EyODc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--2f7cb27acd923627759ae34481bd786abee15c62" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxrWlRBMU1HWTNOeTFpTnpobUxUUmlPVEF0WVdNNU9TMWtNRGd4WW1VeE0yRXlPRGNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--3a61c4c7d57aba635bede7c5f0b5ff4244d1e34e/IMG_2666.jpg" filename="IMG_2666.jpg" filesize="122262" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="The mighty, rugged Prius is just about full up."></action-text-attachment><br><br>I'm grateful to be able to go on this trip, and grateful for the love and support from all of you.  I'm looking forward to stepping away from my day-to-day life for a couple of weeks, to be getting married -- and saving on health insurance, which was literally part of Carrie's marriage pitch late last year.  We've been together for very-almost ten years, so practicalities sometimes speak up first.  But I did use every one of the eighteen candles that we have floating around our house to later do a real proposal, so not all romance is dead.  <br><br> Anyway, hopefully we can all hang out soon.  Thanks for your time, and for your attention.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lZDViYjBiMS04N2VhLTQyODUtOGJlYS1mODY2MDJmZDI5NjE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--3f66fb2bd52b192df5cc780982e4f71120bb307c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsWkRWaVlqQmlNUzA0TjJWaExUUXlPRFV0T0dKbFlTMW1PRFkyTURKbVpESTVOakVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--096d9a3743870153d1d27148ceb1edeea9ea7d19/IMG_2668.jpg" filename="IMG_2668.jpg" filesize="156189" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="Thanks also to Caroline, for this great (chocolate!) banana bread breakfast."></action-text-attachment></div>	Post	13561a03-fdef-4d5f-b219-f8e61450f2dc	2020-10-09 04:30:13.961283	2020-10-09 04:30:15.312981
18b68464-c841-41e1-9a61-71b95d4c0b46	content	<h1>Driving</h1><div>We'd originally planned to stop in Oklahoma City, but found a <a href="https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/36132897?source_impression_id=p3_1602245522_FVQ5nmO%2BJ%2Bbws4tm">cute airbnb</a> in Bristow which is about an hour or so closer.  Somehow an eleven hour drive really is much nicer than a twelve hour drive.  We set out at eight from a sunny Chicago.<br><br>We took a fair number of car trips when we were young and for a while we really only listened to two things over and over -- "500 Miles" by the Proclaimers, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jay_O%27Callahan">story tapes by Jay O'Callahan</a>.  I'm not sure which of those my mom or dad preferred less, but my brother and I are still alive today -- so repeated high-pitched calls of "Again!  Again!" each time "500 Miles" ended were not enough to cause them to take the car violently off of the road and into whatever field of cows or crops was nearby.<br><br>My mom, Elisa, gave us two beautiful gifts:  a couple of Jay O'Callahan CDs, and the perfect mixtape.  We listened to the mixtape first.  It contains fifteen tracks, and all of them are "500 Miles" by the Proclaimers.<br><br><strong>500 Miles Listen Count: 2</strong><br><br>We also listened to one of the Jay O'Callahan stories -- a two-disk piece called "Gouda."  It was great, but I'm really excited for another, "Woe is me Bones."  I can't find a preview, but it's <a href="https://www.ocallahan.com/listen-to-a-story">something like these</a>.<br><br></div><h1>Our Tour of St. Louis</h1><div>Chicago to St. Louis is not an exciting drive, but we were rewarded with a whirlwind tour of the famous Arch.  Witness, in all its glory:<br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9kMTM5YTk1ZS1hY2RkLTQ1ZDItYTUyZi0xZjY5YmQxZTcyOTM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--9d3de1820b66c3665be38d131e1bf5dd5fdc4549" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxrTVRNNVlUazFaUzFoWTJSa0xUUTFaREl0WVRVeVppMHhaalk1WW1ReFpUY3lPVE1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--eb19428a903a9091d2525596abe7f8398a51866f/IMG_2669.jpg" filename="IMG_2669.jpg" filesize="113695" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="So Grand!"></action-text-attachment><br><br>We did actually get a bit closer.  I went up in the arch once as a kid.  It's a terrifying process as the ancient elevator grinds upward, periodically clunking, clanging, adjusting side-to-side to deal with the Arch's angle.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83YWY0YTM2Yy0yZGIyLTQwODEtYTY3Ni0zNzA0ODA4Nzc5NTg_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d27dd37de6bb7371a283b92c4d1e3b3240e81110" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszWVdZMFlUTTJZeTB5WkdJeUxUUXdPREV0WVRZM05pMHpOekEwT0RBNE56YzVOVGdHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c6000bfd1e18ed9795edc4111dc9196fbe0d42ec/IMG_2675.jpg" filename="IMG_2675.jpg" filesize="67326" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie took a bunch of shots looking for the perfect one.  This is it."></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Getting Outside</h1><div>We decided to stretch our legs for a couple of hours at <a href="https://mostateparks.com/park/castlewood-state-park">Castlewood State Park</a>.  We were originally also going to visit <a href="https://www.tripadvisor.com/Attraction_Review-g44881-d3179283-Reviews-Lone_Elk_Park-Saint_Louis_Missouri.html">Lone Elk Park</a> -- where you can see at least one Elk -- but the hike was a bit longer than we anticipated.  At Castlewood, anyway, we did get to see a number of squirrels, perhaps a thousand stink bugs, and one small snake!<br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jMmFlYzEyNS1lOWY3LTQ1OGUtOTkxOS03ZTBjZTdjODFkMDQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--9b12bf32cc4ab6d498acd931d08254e614d605fc" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqTW1GbFl6RXlOUzFsT1dZM0xUUTFPR1V0T1RreE9TMDNaVEJqWlRkak9ERmtNRFFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--1c59754937348828b5e993aeb7d9c1eeaee72c44/IMG_2677.jpg" filename="IMG_2677.jpg" filesize="187046" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="We also saw this river"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hYjIxZTBjOC00MmIzLTQ0NmItYTM0Ni1iZTZlM2Y0NDk0ZTI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--419751630bcc48a825938523b1c0f4f037956569" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxoWWpJeFpUQmpPQzAwTW1JekxUUTBObUl0WVRNME5pMWlaVFpsTTJZME5EazBaVElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--0ec3a8b6f74b58d1123d6ffd8c4242e5fa23da3d/IMG_2679.jpg" filename="IMG_2679.jpg" filesize="141478" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="And a ton of trees"></action-text-attachment><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83NmExM2EzOS04MDFlLTRmNzYtYTUxYi0yMWVkOTFlZGFiNDI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--a6410a7cfbc24ab41c29cf886fbab67cacbf1eeb" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszTm1FeE0yRXpPUzA0TURGbExUUm1Oell0WVRVeFlpMHlNV1ZrT1RGbFpHRmlORElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--682e83ea574498ff7424aa21eab1ca2768972bb2/IMG_2678.jpg" filename="IMG_2678.jpg" filesize="164023" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="And here's proof that we are really there and not just looking up pictures on the internet"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>Getting to Bristow, Oklahoma</h1><div>Our remaining time on Thursday was fairly uneventful, although we did visit <a href="https://www.redmonscandy.com/">Redmond's Candy Factory</a> in order to replace some chocolate pretzels that mysteriously disappeared from our home coincident with Carrie's mom leaving our place last weekend.  We also found out that Oklahoma has toll roads, and Carrie experienced Hardee's curly fries for the first time.<br><br>We're now going to make some coffee, eat a small breakfast that our kind airbnb hosts left, and get back on the road bound for Albuquerque -- whose spelling I have to look up every single time.</div>	Post	68571b2d-caf1-474b-bcf1-94e7a027cc00	2020-10-09 12:57:42.749574	2020-10-09 12:57:42.828329
