InB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--7ce2290916a0de7b6b8df8d9df7153ff2fa6da31/IMG_2831.jpg" filename="IMG_2831.jpg" filesize="148652" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption='Carrie contemplates a mountain, "quite big!"'></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>The Rugged Prius</h1><div><br>Carrie has coined the phrase <em>Rugged Prius, </em>and it's only a quarter jokingly.  It's carried us the whole two thousand miles out to California and we've only had to cut the two plastic pieces from the bottom.  We've sent a few of these to our friends Ben and Allison, who have their own rugged midnight-purple Subaru with which we've been camping out in the midwestern wilderness.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lZDZkNDM2YS1iODJjLTRiYzMtOTQ3NS01Mzk2MTQ5YjQ2NTk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--22a99fb543196ca52344c40f2569618a00de4762" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsWkRaa05ETTJZUzFpT0RKakxUUmlZek10T1RRM05TMDFNemsyTVRRNVlqUTJOVGtHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--f4220099b464070a25eda0141ac0e0d12227e6af/IMG_2834.jpg" filename="IMG_2834.jpg" filesize="135260" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="so rugged"></action-text-attachment><br><br>It did, however, bottom out on an extremely bumpy "dirt" (really, it was a ton of bumpy rocks) road near the top of Tioga Pass just after this picture was taken, so I suppose there are <em>some things</em> it cannot do.<br><br></div><h1>Last Things</h1><div>Here's Tioga Pass, at 9400 feet.  You can see some of the wildfire haze off in the distance.  It's much much more beautiful than our pictures can convey.  We were racing the sun to the pass itself, and got through just around sunset.<br><br>Afterward, we still had about two hours of driving through Yosemite to our cabin in Wawona.  It was dark and the road was extremely curvy, which is fun for thirty minutes and then less fun for another hour and a half.  We made it, tired and happy.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80MDM2MDRhNC0yYzgyLTRkZjYtYmNlZS01YmFkM2RkMTU5ZDQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--4edebaa8de5e2e7d9d81d55ce6f53c157bc33862" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswTURNMk1EUmhOQzB5WXpneUxUUmtaall0WW1ObFpTMDFZbUZrTTJSa01UVTVaRFFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--133c5d72ab2d86f2e7fba0725cbbe5696b087cb8/IMG_2836.jpg" filename="IMG_2836.jpg" filesize="168970" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="there's a lake up there"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80ZTAyZmFkOC05MTdjLTRkMmQtYTEyMC01ZjM4YWJhYjU0MjM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--9f33653f583cb52042850067e93b6c770df7beed" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswWlRBeVptRmtPQzA1TVRkakxUUmtNbVF0WVRFeU1DMDFaak00WVdKaFlqVTBNak1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--367fc389888fd7bae6b01ea5cead1d1b06c1c1c1/IMG_2837.jpg" filename="IMG_2837.jpg" filesize="59745" width="640" height="142" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="it's very wide"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hZDgxYmQ0Yy05ZGY2LTQ3OWEtYTc2Ny0xMmQxMDZhNmVkZjE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--85c855e1b0854399758fada82296d696ca663700" content-type="image/jpeg" 