fcc56153-c339-4d06-b93e-8848b520496e	content	<h1>Early Morning</h1><div><br>We were scheduled to meet Amber, our photographer/guide with <a href="https://adventureinstead.com/">Adventure Instead</a> at 5:20am so that we could hike up to Inspiration Point for a sunrise ceremony.  That meant getting up around 3:30 to leave by 4:30 since we had a bit of a drive.  Carrie headed to bed around eight, and I was up until ten or so.  It wasn't too hard to wake up; we were excited.<br><br>We met Amber in a deserted parking lot at Tunnel View; named either for the dramatic "tunnel" view of the valley -- sheer cliffs rising to either side -- or because it's right next to a long tunnel straight through one of the mountains.  I'm not sure which.  We'd packed our fancy clothes, plus a breakfast picnic and a few other odds-and-ends into my new backpacking backpack.<br><br>Amber, who was awesome throughout the whole day, took a couple of long-exposure shots of us under the stars before we set out.  The hike up was fun -- very dark -- and a little strenuous; it's 1.2 miles with right at 1000 feet of elevation gain.  Headlamps were helpful, although we still ended up veering off the trail a few times, which prompted Amber to call out "uh it's actually this way!" to set us on the right path.<br><br>Amber took photos both with her professional equipment -- which we'll get to see sometime (hopefully!) soon after they're edited -- and with an iphone.  Everything in this post (except the dinner/cake shots of us at the end of the day) was taken by her on the phone and sent over to Carrie so that we'd have some pictures to look at, and share, immediately.<br><br>I'll say out front that I've shrunk these photos a ton so that this journal page loads quickly.  We'll have the original high-res photos (along with the originals of all of the rest of the pictures we've taken) in a gallery somewhere after we get back.<br><br></div><h1>Ceremony</h1><div><br>The view from Inspiration Point is incredible.  We got there maybe twenty minutes before sunrise so we had enough time to change -- Carrie into her dress, myself into my suit.  I forgot my tie, but I don't think it mattered too much.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83Yzc3NmRmNC04Yjk5LTQzYTEtYTExOC0zNGFlYjE5Y2I5ZTc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--b5f7bcd9ebe00272408176ecc548cd654aeafe67" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszWXpjM05tUm1OQzA0WWprNUxUUXpZVEV0WVRFeE9DMHpOR0ZsWWpFNVkySTVaVGNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--45a3d1ae6a196c21ec42c4512fdc545a82ab476e/IMG_0157.jpg" filename="IMG_0157.jpg" filesize="445992" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="some trees that stood witness"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82MjRiZGRkNy02NWNjLTRkODAtYWY4Mi1lNzA1YjBkZGQxZTE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--8e1d8ee90a601f0669b1af673b55432460519977" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyTWpSaVpHUmtOeTAyTldOakxUUmtPREF0WVdZNE1pMWxOekExWWpCa1pHUXhaVEVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--d598e6fe6d308bafa9b90a71b9dc465e94956d19/IMG_0155.jpg" filename="IMG_0155.jpg" filesize="331372" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="wowee zowee"></action-text-attachment><br><br>We wrote shared vows, and each had a little something else to say in addition.  We read a beautiful letter from Tess (Carrie's mom), as well as a card and wonderful ceremony offering from Elisa (Truman's mom).  Pictures of those will be included later on.  Thank you, too, to everyone that left kind thoughts here on our website.  It's meant a ton to read them, and we've loved seeing the responses to our rambling posts.<br><br>We had to pause a few times to jump around and warm up -- the breeze up there was brisk.  We did also record the whole ceremony on video.  Here are the things we promised to each other. We'd love for you to please help hold us to them:<br><br></div><blockquote>We tend to carry love only as a<br>notion that brushes against our lives.<br>I have felt it for you countless times over<br>the past ten years:  over coffee, in warm blankets,<br>under tall trees, and with our small orange gremlin cat.<br>I have felt it for myself, and I have felt it for<br>many that I wish could be with us today.<br><br>But love is too important to be left nebulous.<br>And so I ask for help from Bell Hooks to frame<br>love as something that I can better know and promise.<br>Love is an act of will.  It is both an intention<br>and an action. It is the will to extend one's self<br>for the purpose of nurturing one's own or another's<br>spiritual growth.  I promise both intention and action,<br>to myself and to you.<br><br>I promise to take care of myself so that I may help<br>to take care of you.  I promise to be present and invite<br>you in to my dreams, and fears, and needs.  I promise to<br>accept your invitation, too.  I promise<br>to do when you cannot, and to ask you to do when I cannot.<br>I promise to try to be better tomorrow than I was today,<br>and to help you to do so, too.<br><br>I know love and I vow love, but love remains a<br>deep and powerful mystery.  And so I ask for help<br>from ee cummings to describe what I have come to know:<br><br>here is the deepest secret nobody knows<br>(here is the root of the root and the bud of the bud<br>and the sky of the sky of a tree called life; which grows<br>higher than soul can hope or mind can hide)<br>and this is the wonder that's keeping the stars apart<br><br>i carry your heart (i carry it in my heart)</blockquote><div><br>Afterward we exchanged rings, had a nice picnic break (thanks Caroline for the loan of the blanket, it was perfect!) and then hiked back down to our car.  Carrie bundled up her wedding dress and tucked it into her backpack straps.  It still kicked up a <em>lot</em> of dust.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hZDU0NDkxMi05ZDNkLTQ0YWUtYmY1MC0xNjI3YzVmY2Y1YzA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--347ddc5e5d5bd9573c3a4fd1503f8243da9bee4e" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxoWkRVME5Ea3hNaTA1WkROa0xUUTBZV1V0WW1ZMU1DMHhOakkzWXpWbVkyWTFZekFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c1f5ff5b22a581c9ff3e976969219d422567ed4a/IMG_0165.jpg" filename="IMG_0165.jpg" filesize="604387" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="both Amber and I thought these looked like bell bottoms"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jNDFkN2Q3My1kNjQzLTRmNTMtOWZhZS1iNTIxMjcwNjVjMWY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--322ad3143c45a022b0e06be8b7ae5f8d91c6f6e7" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqTkRGa04yUTNNeTFrTmpRekxUUm1OVE10T1daaFpTMWlOVEl4TWpjd05qVmpNV1lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--06f71a41a5d0dfeb94261c1459fe92f5db192298/IMG_0168.jpg" filename="IMG_0168.jpg" filesize="410798" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="tunnel view (but it's probably named for the literal tunnel, right?)"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82OGVkODI1My0yMTY1LTQ3NDItODJhNi1kN2IyZWMwNzExYmI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--8b2b4de98b297b8d6d2684479303e0f913d256db" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyT0dWa09ESTFNeTB5TVRZMUxUUTNOREl0T0RKaE5pMWtOMkl5WldNd056RXhZbUlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--1e59844aacba89cdc6790bd610a642099f4bbae6/IMG_0170.jpg" filename="IMG_0170.jpg" filesize="397087" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="fancy hiking outfits"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8xY2NjNWMxNy1iMDI2LTQ5MzYtOTU1Ny0zNWY3ODk2NGZkZTI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--fc1df742b649395b790a29c11862bc871ff1722d" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt4WTJOak5XTXhOeTFpTURJMkxUUTVNell0T1RVMU55MHpOV1kzT0RrMk5HWmtaVElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--d8e52b86b803f417dbd8723e6f2c3d8b7a585db4/IMG_0174.jpg" filename="IMG_0174.jpg" filesize="236987" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="hey look at those two sharp dressed folks"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Tuolumne Grove</h1><div><br>We still had about a half of the day left with Amber, so after hiking down we headed to the Tuolumne and Merced groves.  A lot of folks seemed tickled that we'd gotten married in Yosemite -- we got a ton of "congratulations!" and a few folks asked to take pictures for their own personal trip documentation.  My favorite comment followed another couple telling us "Good luck on your marriage!" -- this long-haired guy said under his breath "you don't need luck" before getting into a camper that had "362 days since Florida!" written on the back.<br><br>Tuolumne Grove was about forty minutes from Tunnel View, which as a nice driving break.  Also Yosemite is gigantic.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8yMmI5M2Q3Zi1mY2M4LTQxMGUtYjI0YS0zYjk0YTlhMzcyYWM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--db067d276a4297dbac78c4f46f8c115a23ead696" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt5TW1JNU0yUTNaaTFtWTJNNExUUXhNR1V0WWpJMFlTMHpZamswWVRsaE16Y3lZV01HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--cab0c2c24fd525c38b3efd839275eefd43c8b959/IMG_0179.jpg" filename="IMG_0179.jpg" filesize="678404" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="I love these huge trees"></action-text-attachment><br>We hiked down to the grove -- about a mile or so and another five or six hundred feet of elevation change -- and then toured some of the famous trees.  This is called a tunnel tree, perhaps you can guess why:<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9mYWQyOTU1ZC00ZDU5LTQwYTAtOWRlMy1mMWY3N2RkNTZiYmE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--7925c2815c77d9e598bf69d24d98f85b9e264551" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxtWVdReU9UVTFaQzAwWkRVNUxUUXdZVEF0T1dSbE15MW1NV1kzTjJSa05UWmlZbUVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--ee2db0b4b3daf7c494ed96ab478b78781f0a58ff/IMG_0182.jpg" filename="IMG_0182.jpg" filesize="596141" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="it's because it's within sight of a tunnel that cuts through a mountain"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Tuolumne Grove was pretty busy, but it afforded us the opportunity to wrangle a stranger into signing our marriage license as a witness.  Thanks John!<br><br></div><h1>Merced Grove</h1><div><br>Merced Grove is very close to Tuolumne Grove, but it's way way quieter.  We saw a couple of folks at the trailhead, who warned us that the path was pretty dusty (Carrie's dress was -- as Amber put it -- already a "Yosemite Ombre" by this time).  The grove itself comes after another mile and a half, and another six hundred feet of elevation change.  It was on the way back that my legs really started to feel sore.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80YTg1ZjVhMi1kZDM3LTQ4ZTktODkxOC0zYjdmNDRjNmRhOGI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--1c68e87c68a78220e5a5cdc44442b58ec0124dfd" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswWVRnMVpqVmhNaTFrWkRNM0xUUTRaVGt0T0RreE9DMHpZamRtTkRSak5tUmhPR0lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--5b33f826750015ccae8030d7cfaf1b21c2470bc3/IMG_0187.jpg" filename="IMG_0187.jpg" filesize="571232" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="the blur on this photo is pretty neat"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84NDEyNDQzYy03Y2VkLTQxNDQtOWFmYy02M2Q3MjhhMjZmM2Q_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--661888ed9d55cd24388ffcaca1d090c5a41bc2f1" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TkRFeU5EUXpZeTAzWTJWa0xUUXhORFF0T1dGbVl5MDJNMlEzTWpoaE1qWm1NMlFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--0435fb98210d0391e67a6b4a37fb23b421afa586/IMG_0188.jpg" filename="IMG_0188.jpg" filesize="649901" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="you can't tell but I am looking quite spacey at this point"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84NDdiNWJlYS0xNzVkLTRjZDAtYWEyMC00MmUyZjZmMDM2OGQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d61c4e6a1afa3d1c6865419615590b2755751c7d" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TkRkaU5XSmxZUzB4TnpWa0xUUmpaREF0WVdFeU1DMDBNbVV5WmpabU1ETTJPR1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--441713b57ab847d68ecfc2fde61b94be0f6caeef/IMG_0191.jpg" filename="IMG_0191.jpg" filesize="774118" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="the path itself is also gorgeous"></action-text-attachment><br><br>We were alone for the whole hike, except for a family that we saw on the way back up.  It was quiet, majestic, and humbling.  There was also a neat cabin down near the grove.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lMmU0MzM2YS1lZDdkLTQyZjUtYTY2NS00YzI4ZTU5MDc1NTY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--03269b1c966e4187004679fa214e8a9959a0b5fa" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsTW1VME16TTJZUzFsWkRka0xUUXlaalV0WVRZMk5TMDBZekk0WlRVNU1EYzFOVFlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--cf46f38a031101cc85fd4ba7188fbe3e3aa32ab9/IMG_0193.jpg" filename="IMG_0193.jpg" filesize="696723" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="no idea what this is for"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>The End</h1><div><br>We returned from the Merced Grove hike around 2:30 or 3:00 and our time with Amber was up.  She -- and all of the Adventure Instead folks that we interacted with -- was awesome.<br><br>Afterward we returned to our cabin in Wawona.  We grilled some chicken and summer squash, and roasted potatoes for dinner.  The cabin had a fire table, which is like a table that is 40% less convenient to use (although it does look cool).<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80NzI0YWEzOS04Y2E5LTRhMDUtOGNjMC00NTI1ZmNkNjA1Y2M_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d61a8c6fa52c0ffa125fe273e96448fe23356afa" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswTnpJMFlXRXpPUzA0WTJFNUxUUmhNRFV0T0dOak1DMDBOVEkxWm1Oa05qQTFZMk1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--84bba8460eb876f4d66d50a3270740ae2cfea46b/IMG_2888.jpg" filename="IMG_2888.jpg" filesize="199279" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="so much flame right by your forehead!"></action-text-attachment><br><br>And then we finally ate cake.  I was excited for this part.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80OTkzNDI5MC1mYWU2LTRhOTctOTVhNS04MjQ2NDE5MTBkMWQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--22a8b6ed00e19848c16eabc26a7ee704b1a392c5" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswT1Rrek5ESTVNQzFtWVdVMkxUUmhPVGN0T1RWaE5TMDRNalEyTkRFNU1UQmtNV1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--525ba4c74c599d9837868018a97d737365e533aa/IMG_2890.jpg" filename="IMG_2890.jpg" filesize="284498" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="pretty cake"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83YTdmNGFhMi04MzQwLTRkMmEtYjdjNC1kZTVmYzA0MjAyMjA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--fb8ffcf96783a520f3c13492c1d9b67743c75c47" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszWVRkbU5HRmhNaTA0TXpRd0xUUmtNbUV0WWpkak5DMWtaVFZtWXpBME1qQXlNakFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--90970051a3ea19e20071302fd1165f018b0faf9d/IMG_2893.jpg" filename="IMG_2893.jpg" filesize="263232" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="my expression tells the real tale:  favorite part of the day"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Carrie convinced me to soak in the hot tub briefly (I felt that we were preparing ourselves as lobsters for the surrounding bears), and then we called it a day.<br><br></div><h1>Thank you again</h1><div><br>For all of the love and support you've shown us, and for following along here.  We're not done yet -- we've got Lone Pine (where they shot the movie Tremors!), Death Valley, and the Grand Canyon yet to visit, and we're not due back in Chicago until the weekend of October 24th.  So you'll have several more delayed posts coming your way after this one.<br><br>We miss you all.<br><br>Love,<br><br>Truman &amp; Carrie<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84Y2NhNjMxMi1jZjVlLTQ0YjMtYTQwYS1jZGUzN2RhMTY2MWM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--5872661affb45c726a391980590ea66274c8ff18" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0WTJOaE5qTXhNaTFqWmpWbExUUTBZak10WVRRd1lTMWpaR1V6TjJSaE1UWTJNV01HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--eeb1af0cb3f52d368a72c8b36ee4f2c4dca7f3fe/IMG_0161.jpg" filename="IMG_0161.jpg" filesize="408129" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="you know, hiking is pretty tiring"></action-text-attachment><br><br><br></div>	Post	7938b9a3-b295-472a-919e-17e913330f23	2020-10-15 07:44:17.863071	2020-10-15 07:44:18.45609
