9ebf2796-b4e7-4f46-abae-292b4f04b938	content	<h1>A Change of Plans</h1><div><br>Rather than head down to Sequoia, which is still sort of on fire / extremely smoke-filled, Carrie and I decided to head to Lone Pine, CA, which is sort of in-between Yosemite and Death Valley.  This meant we had a good chunk of the day to check out Yosemite because our drive was only about five hours -- and it also meant we'd get to travel back through Tioga Pass.  I won't call Yosemite's western entrance a total garbage pile (though Carrie may, because it's incredibly winding), but the pass is still the most wonderful part of our trip.<br><br></div><h1>Taft Point &amp; Fissures</h1><div><br>Mostly on our way out of the park was Taft Point (&amp; Fissures), which is a big old rock ledge with huge, huge fissures running through it, after about a mile and a half through some real nice trees.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84NTcwZTMzNS1kYTYwLTQ2YzktOWUzOS03MGMzMzQ0OGY4OTQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--282da67164a05aa96f2ec3c345e8dcf4fb6b6ca0" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TlRjd1pUTXpOUzFrWVRZd0xUUTJZemt0T1dVek9TMDNNR016TXpRME9HWTRPVFFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--b1e97e589d2e66e10a73b88085abec5521656d75/IMG_2900.jpg" filename="IMG_2900.jpg" filesize="438290" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="the trees are so bright"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83OTMzZWY3ZS0wNTQxLTRjNmMtODRlYi02OTgwYjAyZDUwOGY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--3eb248062d400afec4fb79cb88b65966d3642e5b" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszT1RNelpXWTNaUzB3TlRReExUUmpObU10T0RSbFlpMDJPVGd3WWpBeVpEVXdPR1lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--82d225be7d038967a2ccd61fe1abd562cce04031/IMG_2907.jpg" filename="IMG_2907.jpg" filesize="111200" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="I really like portrait mode"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Taft Point itself opens to a large rock-and-scrub plateau after emerging from the trees.  Deep fissures scar the sides of the plateau.  They're so big.<br><br></div><div><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82YWEwYmYxYS1lZTc2LTQ4NWItYTIyMS0wOWFkMTJlNTNmY2I_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--3af59cf0f1a6876e40c55dc6999082cda2db4201" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyWVdFd1ltWXhZUzFsWlRjMkxUUTROV0l0WVRJeU1TMHdPV0ZrTVRKbE5UTm1ZMklHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--affa56910e3644cc77ec465d8dd0628e125c02b2/IMG_2912.jpg" filename="IMG_2912.jpg" filesize="377683" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="you could fit like a hundred Carries into that fissure"></action-text-attachment><br><br>The point itself is a sheer, straight drop-off of like 3000 feet.  No pictures do justice to how nervous this whole situation made me.  I'm not a big fan of heights.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85ODkwOTE5Mi01OGI4LTQ3MWQtYmE5ZC0xYTg4MmEzMWI3NzM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--1824344162db7a1404f1cc195437879505853d22" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1T0Rrd09URTVNaTAxT0dJNExUUTNNV1F0WW1FNVpDMHhZVGc0TW1Fek1XSTNOek1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--72a13868ef1585eb6d89bda0911771fce8a2c335/IMG_2920.jpg" filename="IMG_2920.jpg" filesize="256712" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="just straight down if you look over this cliff"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Other folks don't seem to have this problem.  There were a group of folks hanging out on a ledge, cheering each other on as they slack-lined across part of the point.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iYWQ4MDFkZi02NjliLTRjMjktYTY3ZS0wNTIxNDI5MzQwNDg_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--1e5f4673f8a4af76b267d0bc337646263e8e8997" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpWVdRNE1ERmtaaTAyTmpsaUxUUmpNamt0WVRZM1pTMHdOVEl4TkRJNU16UXdORGdHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--6d00a47af0fd90ce925d5b0ff2a455da7dd451e1/IMG_2917.jpg" filename="IMG_2917.jpg" filesize="240669" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="center-left is a crazy person"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zMzhiYzk1OS04ZWUzLTQ3MDItYWRlYi01MjkxYWI5ZjZiZWI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--0536a97ac279f467b698f993f26581d2c7756548" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6TXpoaVl6azFPUzA0WldVekxUUTNNREl0WVdSbFlpMDFNamt4WVdJNVpqWmlaV0lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--e5bb4f17d8be0999e434210a162dbfcd5c92357b/IMG_2930.jpg" filename="IMG_2930.jpg" filesize="231068" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="we're in a much safer location"></action-text-attachment><br><br>And on our way back, Carrie noticed this incredibly green moss.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80ZDlmMzI1OC1hNzM2LTQ1MGYtYWRmYS1lYmJmZGNhZTQ2NDE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e4ac132425abe51ecf83946f35dd7a2c9a8dc8db" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswWkRsbU16STFPQzFoTnpNMkxUUTFNR1l0WVdSbVlTMWxZbUptWkdOaFpUUTJOREVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--b2a648670548073a50330ef019220a1332a3cc94/IMG_2937.jpg" filename="IMG_2937.jpg" filesize="382023" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="this is much more my speed"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Glacier Point</h1><div><br>You can get to Glacier Point from the Yosemite Valley Floor via the iconic "Four Mile Trail," which is actually 4.8 miles and is 3,200 feet of elevation gain.  Or you can drive along five minutes further from Taft Point, which is what Carrie and I did.  Our guidebook says that you might feel like you "cheated" if you drive rather than climb.  I did not feel this way.<br><br>Glacier Point has incredible views of most of the park.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9mOTQ0MDhkNC1kM2M3LTRiNzItODYzZS1mNTFmMzJkM2E5MmU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--aab9856c6abdc8c4446a5646c4dfdb9e9b93d7d2" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxtT1RRME1EaGtOQzFrTTJNM0xUUmlOekl0T0RZelpTMW1OVEZtTXpKa00yRTVNbVVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--219a0686f8f1aa34eb4dfb4cb3f16a2f22638773/IMG_2942.jpg" filename="IMG_2942.jpg" filesize="334392" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="here's half dome"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80YjdhMTM5Mi1mNDQ0LTQyNzAtYjBjZS05OWUzMzdjZTUxZTI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--6e60ef0862f2a056f4bfcb8c3c01e89df1a932aa" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswWWpkaE1UTTVNaTFtTkRRMExUUXlOekF0WWpCalpTMDVPV1V6TXpkalpUVXhaVElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--9fed0920326631866a80b98f3616fd7815fccc85/IMG_2951.jpg" filename="IMG_2951.jpg" filesize="225003" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="and this is... another mountain"></action-text-attachment><br><br>There's also some wildlife and a gift shop up there.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84MWY0Y2VlYy1lM2VlLTRiN2QtYjA1MC1iYmI4YTFmZThkODk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--1967b16a6a143e9cb75bd1a9e1f7fc099e036f5c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TVdZMFkyVmxZeTFsTTJWbExUUmlOMlF0WWpBMU1DMWlZbUk0WVRGbVpUaGtPRGtHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--324a18222f401208cfab640d53fe66ef400bfd34/20201014_144233.jpg" filename="20201014_144233.jpg" filesize="158535" width="640" height="360" presentation="gallery" caption="Truman captures Carrie capturing a gold-mantled ground squirrel"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Out of the Park</h1><div><br>We took a few minutes on our way out to stop at some of the other sweet spots, including the meadow in front of El Capitan, which is a crazy big mountain that very brave folks climb up.  Including Alex Honnold, who did it without ropes (you should watch <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Free_Solo">Free Solo</a> if you haven't already.)<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hNmEwYTI5Ny00NmZjLTRjNmYtOTY5OS1lNTIwYjNjNWU1ZDY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--78a0b52bbc55207b4ebdb149122857e88c830b94" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxoTm1Fd1lUSTVOeTAwTm1aakxUUmpObVl0T1RZNU9TMWxOVEl3WWpOak5XVTFaRFlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--2ccc64a4504ce04f291b96f402fc751a6c2386d0/IMG_2955.jpg" filename="IMG_2955.jpg" filesize="326769" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="here I am safely on the ground"></action-text-attachment><br><br>El Capitan may look only three or four times taller than I am, but I assure you it's much bigger.  We noticed that the smoke seemed a little worse today, too.  We were very lucky to have great weather and pretty good air quality on our wedding day.<br><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84YTMyOTRkMy00YTNlLTRmN2UtOTcyZi01NDE3ZTU3MjhlZWE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--048709344662a722dbdecb6d2219107f2b202d53" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0WVRNeU9UUmtNeTAwWVRObExUUm1OMlV0T1RjeVppMDFOREUzWlRVM01qaGxaV0VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--576b5de1bade5446d013255fb40a24d9bde164a4/IMG_2959.jpg" filename="IMG_2959.jpg" filesize="163669" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="lightning started these"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Here are a few last pictures of us leaving Yosemite (and the Inyo National Forest).  Notice how long Carrie's arms have grown.  I think it's probably the elevation.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi81ZWZkZjk4ZS1mMGQzLTQ5ZGMtYjRmNC1iODcyMjQzMmM5NzA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--724922ff827cab576faa9f3af69fa5df9651a71f" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsxWldaa1pqazRaUzFtTUdRekxUUTVaR010WWpSbU5DMWlPRGN5TWpRek1tTTVOekFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--24c72bb515f1853eaa1a5ed487895e296ebf4dcd/IMG_2962.jpg" filename="IMG_2962.jpg" filesize="62540" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="carrie and a mountain"></action-text-attachment><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8xNTI0ZjI1ZS1jMTYwLTQxYTAtOTE4ZC1lYzJlMmUxZDhlYzE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--179095aad070be2dad0a9051680df922aa7deaf0" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt4TlRJMFpqSTFaUzFqTVRZd0xUUXhZVEF0T1RFNFpDMWxZekpsTW1VeFpEaGxZekVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--90aa86a396e1ffacf12399f1c28b36d537e0d5b9/IMG_2967.jpg" filename="IMG_2967.jpg" filesize="315094" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="truman and carrie and a mountain (and some trees)"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lYWI3Njc5OC0wMzRkLTRmNDgtOGZkMi03NWM4Mjg0ZGUzMGQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e5dba60de9cfd9b598a2784190a7579bd5aadd25" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsWVdJM05qYzVPQzB3TXpSa0xUUm1ORGd0T0daa01pMDNOV000TWpnMFpHVXpNR1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--872282cd963e888ebff569afda0c8101ef6c677c/IMG_2986.jpg" filename="IMG_2986.jpg" filesize="344422" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="near the entrance to Yosemite"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zZGZjZGIzZS03MGY1LTQyOTAtYjk2MC03MzFkZWI4MGRkMWE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--7e1f919f0a500f6b343755df41598c22562738d3" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6WkdaalpHSXpaUzAzTUdZMUxUUXlPVEF0WWprMk1DMDNNekZrWldJNE1HUmtNV0VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--1d5c74ea1e2f3ecd46e4eebae34f58b0a01102fb/IMG_2991.jpg" filename="IMG_2991.jpg" filesize="291121" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="like an alien"></action-text-attachment></div>	Post	227bf4fd-a908-406d-8592-4975bc0d1a16	2020-10-18 01:38:36.247913	2020-10-18 01:38:37.230617
5037aef0-d216-476c-aac4-838ce4e87d02	content	<h1>Lone Pine</h1><div><br>Lone Pine is a small town just east of the Sierra Navada mountains, about an hour or so outside of Death Valley.  It's also near the Alabama Hills, which are famous as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lone_Pine,_California#Film_history_at_Lone_Pine">setting for movies</a> such as Tremors (with the esteemed Kevin Bacon), and many other lesser-known films.  On the way to Lone Pine are two other sites:  <a href="https://www.nps.gov/manz/index.htm">Manzanar</a>, one of the WWII Japanese detainment camps; and the <a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/inyo/specialplaces/?cid=stelprdb5129900">Ancient Bristlecone Pine Forest</a>, home to the oldest single living thing we've been able to measure.  Unfortunately Carrie and I did not get to stop at either of these places -- they'll have to be for the next grand roadtrip.<br><br>In brighter news, however, our <a href="https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/12407656">awesome airbnb</a> was filled with cat things.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lODMzZjM4ZS04ZDZlLTRjYzEtOTJlZi1hZTc3Nzg1ZTVlMGI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--80eb2ba22596e9dcf6b45bd10233273f4fc1df15" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsT0RNelpqTTRaUzA0WkRabExUUmpZekV0T1RKbFppMWhaVGMzTnpnMVpUVmxNR0lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--893bdf5765177c611f3a49968a4d608dcfaf8125/IMG_2996.jpg" filename="IMG_2996.jpg" filesize="208340" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Lone Pine sits right between the Sierra Nevada and Inyo Mountains"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82YjA3MDVjMy1kYWU0LTRhNzMtYTcyMS02ZjY3YzNmYmU5Yzc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--804d5e531e69b95f61a258aeef1d2bfbd6b22d0a" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyWWpBM01EVmpNeTFrWVdVMExUUmhOek10WVRjeU1TMDJaalkzWXpObVltVTVZemNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--607c4559807f543d2c5ec999176bedfd45770a3e/IMG_3009.jpg" filename="IMG_3009.jpg" filesize="206038" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="cat things!"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8yMzgzZjNmMC01NDE5LTRlMjYtYjczOC0yZWUyZGFhMWQyZDI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--385a0e8da16c62c5f9dda8b2d9de896f0fe35930" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt5TXpnelpqTm1NQzAxTkRFNUxUUmxNall0WWpjek9DMHlaV1V5WkdGaE1XUXlaRElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--a265b623842db58d77b82e7ba751801e11862a1b/IMG_3011.jpg" filename="IMG_3011.jpg" filesize="262050" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="cat things!"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Our host, Robert, also promised to mail us some of Lone Pine's locally roasted coffee (it's featured in the airbnb listing, but was unavailable when we visited).  Great place, great host.<br><br></div><h1>Alabama Hills</h1><div><br>Carrie and I headed in to the Alabama Hills to try to get a glimpse of the filming location of Kevin Bacon's famed "Tremors."  Unfortunately the road ("Movie Road") was closed, so we had to turn around and climb on some rocks instead.  It's maybe not my best decision to skitter around boulders without a helmet or safety equipment, but there were a fair number of people around so I probably wouldn't have to <em>one-hundred-twenty-seven hours</em> myself.  Plus it allowed us to take some sick rock-acrobat photos.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hOGI5MTNmNS02NzAxLTQyMGEtOWNkMC1iODAyNGJlNWYxYmE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--f2e7f185e77949adbc41849cb94f0b812fc28815" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxoT0dJNU1UTm1OUzAyTnpBeExUUXlNR0V0T1dOa01DMWlPREF5TkdKbE5XWXhZbUVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--77348633c8552589c5244c1788042633242c2c41/IMG_3017.jpg" filename="IMG_3017.jpg" filesize="261008" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="also we found a rock that looks like a six-toed foot!"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hMWQ3YzA3ZS0yNzg1LTQ4NzQtYTJlYy0xNjhiMjhkOTI3NDY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--0123788787365051d467186bcf9c0261c461a001" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxoTVdRM1l6QTNaUzB5TnpnMUxUUTROelF0WVRKbFl5MHhOamhpTWpoa09USTNORFlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--58672a09c1eedcad0d079a2135610168ff26c0f7/IMG_3019.jpg" filename="IMG_3019.jpg" filesize="90068" width="640" height="147" presentation="gallery" caption="everything in the west is so wide"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82ZDM5YzhkYi00ZmQ1LTQzMmYtYTZjZi1mOGI0N2JhNWY3MDk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--9425885c7016e6a69a49a8db5a2dbc249f8508c8" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyWkRNNVl6aGtZaTAwWm1RMUxUUXpNbVl0WVRaalppMW1PR0kwTjJKaE5XW