find a way around the previously-mentioned roadblock to the historic filming location of the esteemed Tremors, we inadvertently drove halfway up a mountain and found ourselves at the trailhead to summit Mt. Whitney (the highest point in the contiguous United States).  It was beautiful.  We did not summit it.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jOGVjZWE2OS04ZGU0LTQ5NDUtOWFlYS1lZGJjYTkxMTUyNWI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--a4c3f5464c90b4c010872c6ba4edf0c63ab6c64c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqT0dWalpXRTJPUzA0WkdVMExUUTVORFV0T1dGbFlTMWxaR0pqWVRreE1UVXlOV0lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--6db75d5cadcc42746b81023360f03ebaee2263ff/IMG_3065.jpg" filename="IMG_3065.jpg" filesize="631354" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="is *that one* Mt. Whitney?  I could not tell you."></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80NmJkZjdjNC04MTBiLTRjZTQtOTY0YS1hODc2NDQ5NDJkZjE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--faeda0eb5553fd21ac3266033a137f5fe1f7bd6e" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswTm1Ka1pqZGpOQzA0TVRCaUxUUmpaVFF0T1RZMFlTMWhPRGMyTkRRNU5ESmtaakVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--692fcb78c4f27a3644149349c180c804bcefc446/IMG_3051.jpg" filename="IMG_3051.jpg" filesize="682060" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="beautiful camping and a beautiful stream"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8xODVjYjhmZi1lYzc1LTRkYzEtOGUzYS0wNDBmYmFkMzJmODA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--58b43574d2e8f3a38984f41aaef5d6a3d9d02e71" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt4T0RWallqaG1aaTFsWXpjMUxUUmtZekV0T0dVellTMHdOREJtWW1Ga016Sm1PREFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--dbf8c08845f511c7cf109425faa28cc9fef50e45/IMG_3053.jpg" filename="IMG_3053.jpg" filesize="158713" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="what an incredible portrait"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Returning from Mt. Whitney</h1><div><br>We'd just about reached the Alabama Hills at the foot of Mt. Whitney when we started smelling a bad smell.  It wasn't Truman (or Carrie), it was the Rugged Prius.  We got out to see white smoke coming from the break-pads in the wheels.  This is when we remembered about <em>engine breaking</em> and promptly figured out how to spare the poor Rugged Prius' breaks during Rugged Descents.  This would become especially important as we headed down into Death Valley.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jZjkzODYwYy1lODNjLTQ3ZTItOWY5Ny0yNGEyYmFjMTFjZjM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d41ed3d18e1232c5a65412f0ca1a43c4ecffab10" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqWmprek9EWXdZeTFsT0ROakxUUTNaVEl0T1dZNU55MHlOR0V5WW1Gak1URmpaak1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--95d90e63c722e14a98ea3bc49020c67bf7fb4da2/IMG_3061.jpg" filename="IMG_3061.jpg" filesize="693794" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="gross!"></action-text-attachment></div>	Post	393f8cec-0913-41b6-9b02-38570ea59dc0	2020-10-18 02:10:20.365927	2020-10-18 02:10:20.746172
191419ea-a4af-44f1-b9d8-8b7e7df00e2a	content	<h1>Driving In</h1><div><br>Death Valley is gigantic, wide wide open, and beautiful.  I think I've used those adjectives a lot in these posts but the bits of the West that we've been able to see are just so wild (queue <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_zXKtfKnfT8">Will Smith</a>).<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84ZDQ3ZTZiZi1hMGNhLTQ2NzYtOGE4NC05ODMwNzY1YmM3NjQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e196ef626453870e327574a4a7f7c91b3e2a567f" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0WkRRM1pUWmlaaTFoTUdOaExUUTJOell0T0dFNE5DMDVPRE13TnpZMVltTTNOalFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--6cf0837a38f633879a2eadce42f2de2b660edaac/IMG_3068.jpg" filename="IMG_3068.jpg" filesize="202812" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="here we are, definitely not about to die"></action-text-attachment><br><br>On our way, we stopped at the "Star Wars Canyon" on the western edge of the valley.  Apparently pilots use this canyon to develop low-flying dogfighting skills (in Will Smith's case, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LjtAXT2vJAg">against world-destroying aliens</a>).<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80Zjc4NDJkZC1hYzRjLTQxOWUtOWRiNi1hOTZiNDZhMDAzZmY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--8be8e8aa0831fa38dd23138634d71210a03fcfe2" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswWmpjNE5ESmtaQzFoWXpSakxUUXhPV1V0T1dSaU5pMWhPVFppTkRaaE1EQXpabVlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--750680fc474857a6184cba5d16341770d3fe5e39/IMG_3071.jpg" filename="IMG_3071.jpg" filesize="256666" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="we saw neither fighter pilots nor aliens"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Parts of Death Valley look similar to the scrub-and-mountains that we've spent uh at least twenty hours driving through, just much much bigger.  We also put our new Rugged Prius' engine breaking skills to good use.  I had thought that Death Valley was just like a big... valley; mostly flat once you got inside.  It's definitely not.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83NzgwNDdlZC04ODg2LTRlMWUtYmZkNS1kNTUwZjg0MWM4OWY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--fe60db61403b3918270846c0cd348a2fe4c1f4a8" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszTnpnd05EZGxaQzA0T0RnMkxUUmxNV1V0WW1aa05TMWtOVFV3WmpnME1XTTRPV1lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--cea47b58aefeea0bb2a3a48d8e13a794af9b90df/IMG_3082.jpg" filename="IMG_3082.jpg" filesize="306625" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="a whole valley of scrub"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zYWI5MGJjMy1jODFjLTQ5MDgtYmU0NC1mYjE5NzM2MzYwMjY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--6ba14ada6669a6caf618ebf681bed3340e719dd1" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6WVdJNU1HSmpNeTFqT0RGakxUUTVNRGd0WW1VME5DMW1ZakU1TnpNMk16WXdNallHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--8608ba50595aba8f3f0c9dc3e4bdc7ddeef613b0/IMG_3084.jpg" filename="IMG_3084.jpg" filesize="95067" width="640" height="146" presentation="gallery" caption="a whole valley!"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>Camping</h1><div><br>We decided to camp just one night in Death Valley rather than two so that we could get on to the Grand Canyon a bit earlier.  Also because it's hot.  Fortunately we chose to camp at the Wild Rose Campground, up at 4100 feet -- so it was considerably less hot (in the 70s or 80s in the day, 50s or 60s at night).  Wild Rose is first-come first-camp, so we headed there first when we got in around 3pm.  Unfortunately it was at the end of a windy windy eighteen mile road, so by the time we got to set up camp we didn't feel too much like leaving.  But it's a free site, which is pretty nice.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84M2UzYWI2ZS1mN2MyLTRhMGQtYWNmMC0wYmRiZjQ2NmRmN2E_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--0e28de668c544547c87d6bebec96f2701f6b812c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TTJVellXSTJaUzFtTjJNeUxUUmhNR1F0WVdObU1DMHdZbVJpWmpRMk5tUm1OMkVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--2af8ec385fd038aee6490499f5e7f68925c02931/IMG_3087.jpg" filename="IMG_3087.jpg" filesize="304793" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie by our pretty pretty sweet backpacking tent (previously pictured in our apartment with Catballs)"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iZjAxYTNmOC1kY2E0LTQwZjUtYWRmOS04NDU0Nzg1MjFkOGE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--a668626e68a94e4c630dda7350222a8be1b7f33d" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpWmpBeFlUTm1PQzFrWTJFMExUUXdaalV0WVdSbU9TMDRORFUwTnpnMU1qRmtPR0VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--3503f6e66ab902a7c5137f1d98137670d6d6f205/IMG_3095.jpg" filename="IMG_3095.jpg" filesize="241507" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="sunset brings out the colors in the hills"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jMGJiMWQ0OC1iYzMxLTQ1YTgtOTNkZC04Y2UwYjE0N2M1MmQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--70fd0a6988dc7695a003eba4997d4d9fdeb65f9f" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqTUdKaU1XUTBPQzFpWXpNeExUUTFZVGd0T1ROa1pDMDRZMlV3WWpFME4yTTFNbVFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--3b7da1d7bb39fc72d81bd62ea3f643834cf6dea6/IMG_3104.jpg" filename="IMG_3104.jpg" filesize="337765" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie artfully posed while cooking our chicken rice"></action-text-attachment><br><br>A note about chicken rice.  We prepared a number of backpacking meals, as well as some ready-made (but refrigeration required) freeze-dried chicken with prepared rice and quinoa.  The chicken-rice is a curry with dehydrated mushrooms and freeze-dried vegetables.  It's not awful, but it's somehow aggressively bland.  We do not look forward to eating it, but eat it we must.<br><br></div><h1>That Night</h1><div><br>We camped under the Death Valley sky, which was quiet, and dark, and huge.  We'd purposefully chosen our wedding day near a new moon since we knew we'd be in many places with beautiful skies, and Death Valley was the best.  Carrie saw six shooting stars; the milky way was bright against the night.<br><br>Our evening was interrupted, though, deep in the night.  First a rustle and then a loud loud braying -- what sounded just near our tent.  Carrie thought that a mountain lion had caught a donkey in the gulch just below our tent and was having its dinner.  Later we figured that it was instead two <a href="https://www.hcn.org/articles/climate-desk-what-are-wild-burros-doing-to-death-valley">wild donkeys</a> amorously enjoying a not-so-quiet evening to themselves.<br><br></div><h1>The Next Morning</h1><div><br>The best time in Death Valley, Carrie has said at least ten times since our visit, is the morning.  It's cooler, true, but the better feature is the morning light.  We got up before sunrise and drove to Zabriskie Point to try to catch it.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iOTNjYTc2ZS04YWFlLTRhODgtOTNlOC01MmVmNWNmYTc0NWQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--b9af4b5f8207cb02c6e1c7dd006b9d08bdcb6951" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpT1ROallUYzJaUzA0WVdGbExUUmhPRGd0T1RObE9DMDFNbVZtTldObVlUYzBOV1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--83044b6cb51daefd74d7b7f7432e360e6814fe3e/IMG_3110.jpg" filename="IMG_3110.jpg" filesize="196113" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="so vivid"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lNDAxNWNkZS0xOGRmLTQ2M2ItOGQ3Mi1hNzQxZGJjYjI2ZTE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--19e2f065aa705940925fd86dbf99e238b8a23a7b" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsTkRBeE5XTmtaUzB4T0dSbUxUUTJNMkl0T0dRM01pMWhOelF4WkdKallqSTJaVEVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--2cdd54dd85c0f592bcdc6858570235410e6b997b/IMG_3106.jpg" filename="IMG_3106.jpg" filesize="151491" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="is it a bad blurry picture, or is it HIGH ART?!"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9mOWE5ZDEwNC0wZmQ3LTRlNjYtYThjNy1iN2M1NDI4ZjA3MjU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--16b38ddf42cf6bfed56ced5cf8dd0cdd7554e67b" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxtT1dFNVpERXdOQzB3Wm1RM0xUUmxOall0WVRoak55MWlOMk0xTkRJNFpqQTNNalVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--4b251c792c56888eecf8a9c1b3dcf4681151871b/IMG_3116.jpg" filename="IMG_3116.jpg" filesize="207507" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="the hills are alive with beauty"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85NmJlNTM5OC05YTEwLTRjNDEtODY2OS0wMThjZGQwYjQzZjQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--cc9c19de8f85bc38a9c51e4763d9472930324c86" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1Tm1KbE5UTTVPQzA1WVRFd0xUUmpOREV0T0RZMk9TMHdNVGhqWkdRd1lqUXpaalFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--4eba5733bd6a44357cdfbabaed75cebde92144cb/IMG_3124.jpg" filename="IMG_3124.jpg" filesize="289181" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="(and scorpions)"></action-text-attachment><br><br>This was probably the best part of the whole day, although the remaining hiking was fun, too.  It was also extremely windy up on Zabriskie Point.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80NTA1MGY5Yy1jMDFkLTRhNmItYWIwMC1jNDYzMDE3ZjcyNDk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e09beefe3860eac86099eea6e41af03ba9ead287" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswTlRBMU1HWTVZeTFqTURGa0xUUmhObUl0WVdJd01DMWpORFl6TURFM1pqY3lORGtHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c39a9c9c09920d315f6c9d6389d3fc6b2b56bd8b/IMG_3119.jpg" filename="IMG_3119.jpg" filesize="262869" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="my beard is not usually so pointed"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>The Rest of the Day</h1><div><br>After Zabriskie Point, we stopped to make coffee and camping oatmeal and then continued to Badwater Basin, which is the lowest point in America.  Apparently named by a mule driver who stopped there with his team -- he noted that the animals did not want to drink from the water and figured that it was "bad."  A truly majestic story.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi81ZDZlOGVhNC1lYWMxLTQ0OTktYTM5NC03MzQwOWQ1M2VlMjY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--979c513beb3448607a7d889e0ef6e70ebfa54d83" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsxWkRabE9HVmhOQzFsWVdNeExUUTBPVGt0WVRNNU5DMDNNelF3T1dRMU0yVmxNallHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--997a8547b2d145c3ad673811c7b6fc223d94280f/IMG_3132.jpg" filename="IMG_3132.jpg" filesize="65111" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie and Oatmeal -- about 90 degrees at 9am"></action-text-attachment><br><br>We also saw two (live) roadrunners.  Carrie was not driving at the time and so we were able to admire their beauty and so they were allowed to remain alive.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9kN2EwYzE0MS0zODU2LTQ5ODctYmMwNy01NTdjODM0Nzk2OTk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--532ebbbb1e9426005116090c4d913ac61bcd4240" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxrTjJFd1l6RTBNUzB6T0RVMkxUUTVPRGN0WW1Nd055MDFOVGRqT0RNME56azJPVGtHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--868ee8f2fe0b1c627eeec081bf57925633a2d2f2/IMG_3144.jpg" filename="IMG_3144.jpg" filesize="232498" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption='that tiny sign on the rock denotes "sea level"'></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9mY2MxNTRkZC1kZDEyLTQ4MWItYjg0NS03MjY1MzI0ZDFiMTM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--969a5b5726ff3c835bbaf93bcbf31ae2c028b12e" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxtWTJNeE5UUmtaQzFrWkRFeUxUUTRNV0l0WWpnME5TMDNNalkxTXpJMFpERmlNVE1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--fe43a9a52db8ccdc91663c24c88c84df0bcbc79b/IMG_3148.jpg" filename="IMG_3148.jpg" filesize="330838" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="salt flats line the base of badwater basin"></action-text-attachment><br><br>On the way back, we hiked through the Golden Canyon (so named because the rocks are golden-gray, instead of normal-gray like many other Death Valley rocks), and did a bit of off-trail hiking.  A lot of the rocks have wildly supple textures due to erosion.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82NzNiNzRiZi01YTk5LTQ1ZGQtYTBhNS0xNjcxN2JlOWVjM2M_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--f4f6708ef26295dff5f4efd95c5c2b8064cce06c" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyTnpOaU56UmlaaTAxWVRrNUxUUTFaR1F0WVRCaE5TMHhOamN4TjJKbE9XVmpNMk1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--f2a39a79d578f721c23fb38dc9b9a0a2e1b27898/IMG_3158.jpg" filename="IMG_3158.jpg" filesize="399263" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="like the skin of an ancient set of jowls"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iM2I1YjdhYS02NTI0LTRmNjctYjJiNS04MTNiYWUzNTEyOTU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--0ceea10d1a94c450cb842138e5b3dca0a1954ff5" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpTTJJMVlqZGhZUzAyTlRJMExUUm1OamN0WWpKaU5TMDRNVE5pWVdVek5URXlPVFVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--9b6798a25dae118a034dd68b7ad8ca967106724d/IMG_3170.jpg" filename="IMG_3170.jpg" filesize="328850" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="quite dapper with her walking stick"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84N2ZlMzY0NC04N2QxLTQxYzQtYjU2Zi0xMjA0NmMyM2VhOGY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--b2303f8675d67b1b3d3eb1268d201e6e39c51ea2" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TjJabE16WTBOQzA0TjJReExUUXhZelF0WWpVMlppMHhNakEwTm1NeU0yVmhPR1lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--5c1e3ee4dffb3d0605acb9449437dca4f6dc839f/IMG_3174.jpg" filename="IMG_3174.jpg" filesize="82141" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="reappearance of the least urban hat"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>At The End</h1><div><br>Before leaving Death Valley we stopped at one of the high (elevation) points, which offered great views of the valley floor -- as well as a sweet lizard.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82M2QwYTJhYy03NDBiLTQ3NzEtOTRiYS0wMWU3ODU1YWRhZWY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7