fe7424e3-40e5-43c0-9835-8c4c7c6e823b	content	<h1>Williams Arizona</h1><div><br>We passed through <a href="https://experiencewilliams.com/">Williams</a> on our way into the Grand Canyon.  It claims the last Classic Route 66 town to survive before being bypassed by I-40.  It has neon signs everywhere, and incredible Dad Energy.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9mMjhiY2E2Yy1hN2VkLTRjY2UtODk1OC1jZjdjNWE2MzU3ZWU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e4b02f1d0dc494aaa523396737007f778681e33d" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxtTWpoaVkyRTJZeTFoTjJWa0xUUmpZMlV0T0RrMU9DMWpaamRqTldFMk16VTNaV1VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c0b40c118f397c53891b870d118de0cb1bc9ed24/IMG_3198.jpg" filename="IMG_3198.jpg" filesize="216675" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="the entire main drag is lit up like this"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85MWFmM2FhZS0xMzg3LTQ5NWEtOTdmOS1jNDNiMWI5MmUxNjE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--50cbb26919bf400287bdb0f8c756fcfffd8078a8" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1TVdGbU0yRmhaUzB4TXpnM0xUUTVOV0V0T1RkbU9TMWpORE5pTVdJNU1tVXhOakVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--b63a7cc9fc0015e02b9929881e8bd5c01ecaac70/IMG_3199.jpg" filename="IMG_3199.jpg" filesize="201093" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="so many colors"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jODcwZDNkMy1iMjU4LTQxNWYtOGM0YS1lM2NjNzkzYzk1MmE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--f5f68b16c40183e17292ba59853bb1608df0fd36" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqT0Rjd1pETmtNeTFpTWpVNExUUXhOV1l0T0dNMFlTMWxNMk5qTnprell6azFNbUVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--76f0ad17b6c6a57041f5f45d86fb4e9566b64cde/IMG_3201.jpg" filename="IMG_3201.jpg" filesize="196420" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="and a glowing cow!"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>The Grand Canyon</h1><div><br>We decided to stay within the Grand Canyon National Park in order to maximize our chance of getting either a backcountry camping permit, or a walk-up reservation to <a href="https://www.nps.gov/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/grand-canyon-in-depth-03.htm">Phantom Ranch</a>, a lodge at the bottom of the canyon.  Permits for backcountry camping, or reservations for Phantom Ranch, fill up something like a year in advance.  <br><br>Fortunately there are a small number of walk-up permits available, and sometimes folks fail to confirm their stay with Phantom Ranch.  Unfortunately for either you have to get up quite early in order to get your name in.  We put our name for both and, in the meantime, walked a bit of the Grand Canyon rim trail.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi83MDU4YzhlYy04OTA1LTRhZGMtYjU3NS05ODFlZjViNmQyMDM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--3a96b7324be5280afaa7bc2231bea63034030b31" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWszTURVNFl6aGxZeTA0T1RBMUxUUmhaR010WWpVM05TMDVPREZsWmpWaU5tUXlNRE1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--b64e19ae939cfff8819f521bb94736da70e7cc6f/IMG_3202.jpg" filename="IMG_3202.jpg" filesize="317922" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="what a hole!"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8wZTlkNDgzNS02OTVhLTRjOGMtODcyOC0zYWZjNzlkMjVjMTk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--521490ea8d34ab141f5a31093c1a520165b387d0" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt3WlRsa05EZ3pOUzAyT1RWaExUUmpPR010T0RjeU9DMHpZV1pqTnpsa01qVmpNVGtHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--a133fc902d68dce9dfe182b47aaf163f1d7874df/IMG_3203.jpg" filename="IMG_3203.jpg" filesize="326561" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="selfies can be difficult"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iODQ2Yzc4ZS01NDQzLTQ5MjMtOGIwZC0yZWVhOTQ1NWM1MDY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--c51aea67bab765a201b05efc5a2e4f7a518387e2" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpT0RRMll6YzRaUzAxTkRRekxUUTVNak10T0dJd1pDMHlaV1ZoT1RRMU5XTTFNRFlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--6fc8fa9fb56d3b6dd6dad3f902f19eee31bdbc9b/IMG_3228.jpg" filename="IMG_3228.jpg" filesize="440135" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="we also saw an elk!"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Later that afternoon, we got to use our new lightweight frying pan (thanks Harrison and Sara!) to reheat some pizza we'd bought the prior evening -- our room does not have a kitchenette, so we had to improvise.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jMDQ3ZmFiYy02ZjMxLTQ5ZmMtYTM5MS0zZjI4YzhhNGNhYTU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--3f29421b0eb85f6542aeed628d7af2095d9e9380" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqTURRM1ptRmlZeTAyWmpNeExUUTVabU10WVRNNU1TMHpaakk0WXpoaE5HTmhZVFVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--fec0bc89ad6b9f403d872284a01e380454c6370d/IMG_3230.jpg" filename="IMG_3230.jpg" filesize="299181" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="what a setup"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84NjJjZjBiNi04NjY5LTRjMWEtYmQ4Ny05MWE2OWY3ZjA4ODI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--7e879a02871e7d60e456b1cb5845ad54cee07935" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TmpKalpqQmlOaTA0TmpZNUxUUmpNV0V0WW1RNE55MDVNV0UyT1dZM1pqQTRPRElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--11f8710e5d7271a29f95a34d2556d34bdcd47f67/IMG_3232.jpg" filename="IMG_3232.jpg" filesize="235320" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="this actually works really well"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>The Big News</h1><div><br>We were contacted by the backcountry office pretty early with great news -- they have a permit available for us to go hiking down into the canyon!  We're leaving tomorrow morning (Sunday) and returning on Tuesday.  The bottom of the canyon is at about 2,400 feet, which is 4,800 lower than where we are on the south rim -- so the hike is going to be a big drop and a big climb.<br><br>We're planning on going down the shorter (steeper) trail, South Kaibab, which is about 7 miles.  We're returning on the Bright Angel Trail, which totals about 9. 5 miles -- but fortunately we're stopping over at the Indian Garden on Monday evening, which is roughly halfway.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8yNjQzMzczZi1lNmZkLTQ5NzgtODU5Mi02ZTNjMTVlMDQ2OTc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--546d643f7396404611c9a61d564133b479a8276b" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt5TmpRek16Y3paaTFsTm1aa0xUUTVOemd0T0RVNU1pMDJaVE5qTVRWbE1EUTJPVGNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--8211bfdb404893513286e0bcbfb7f7062ee6b517/IMG_3217.jpg" filename="IMG_3217.jpg" filesize="263923" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie contemplates sore legs"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lZWNhZmYwYy1lYzkwLTQzNDItODU0ZC0yYjc1ODY2ODVmMzA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e486dc6b0dfa46e445393ad8e43ce86ce820fa1a" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsWldOaFptWXdZeTFsWXprd0xUUXpOREl0T0RVMFpDMHlZamMxT0RZMk9EVm1NekFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c0b26cde6cde84e3dabae0131ca8d33dbc059f46/IMG_3222.jpg" filename="IMG_3222.jpg" filesize="364776" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="it's pretty big"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84NDU4NDk3ZC0wYzhmLTQyM2UtODIyYS02ZGFhNjcwNDJhMmM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d328babeb8294ef83610ca39bc9380464719d481" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0TkRVNE5EazNaQzB3WXpobUxUUXlNMlV0T0RJeVlTMDJaR0ZoTmpjd05ESmhNbU1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--dbd6d143a9b35eda9bc0c2bfa993b3a07119b252/IMG_3210.jpg" filename="IMG_3210.jpg" filesize="372186" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="here's part of the trail we'll be walking back up on Tuesday"></action-text-attachment><br><br>Carrie and I spent the evening arranging and packing our backpacks.  They're pretty heavy, but hopefully they will help us not die!<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8xMDYzNTY1NS05ZGI3LTQxZWEtYmIzYi05OWIxNDcwNjA3OGE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--aabd1125e144ecca923ba3717c36ff15e54265cf" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt4TURZek5UWTFOUzA1WkdJM0xUUXhaV0V0WW1JellpMDVPV0l4TkRjd05qQTNPR0VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--5f831dbce0eabd3ce6b66dcbc012539ea69bd08a/IMG_3234.jpg" filename="IMG_3234.jpg" filesize="468995" width="853" height="640" presentation="gallery" caption="useful things"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zZDE2NDVlOC1iYTZlLTRmMGEtYjcyNC1lMmM0OTFmMzZiMTc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--ec5704c078fab1650a6f5973e270d3dc84ceb611" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6WkRFMk5EVmxPQzFpWVRabExUUm1NR0V0WWpjeU5DMWxNbU0wT1RGbU16WmlNVGNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--1ae9896bd5e4a5df28fcdb374631a54bcecb0e92/IMG_3233.jpg" filename="IMG_3233.jpg" filesize="301965" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="useful foods"></action-text-attachment><br><br>See you all on Tuesday evening -- wish us luck!<br><br></div>	Post	c8802f2d-aaa5-4840-8586-9d5a3e2b3757	2020-10-18 05:25:30.852102	2020-10-18 05:25:31.299438
