achment><br><br>We saw a ton of these Utah Agave plants, which grow for a long time and then flower as a huge spear and then die.  We also had our second non-lethal sighting of a road runner!<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lNzc0YzRiMy03NDFkLTRhNWQtYjI2ZC1kMDc0MTA3ZDFlNzQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--df642498584cd4cb3e36e8c0d824e0eb9a0eaa45" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsTnpjMFl6UmlNeTAzTkRGa0xUUmhOV1F0WWpJMlpDMWtNRGMwTVRBM1pERmxOelFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--36fa1ab5f481e1a51254922bb46aaebef6b642f7/IMG_3346.jpeg" filename="IMG_3346.jpeg" filesize="354734" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="no inappropriate jokes here"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zNDMwYzhmYy1jMmQzLTRkZTEtYWZjNC0yMDFmNjE0YTQwZjU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--996075495a0967f52d26c952db7fcc5385a7dc05" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6TkRNd1l6aG1ZeTFqTW1RekxUUmtaVEV0WVdaak5DMHlNREZtTmpFMFlUUXdaalVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--81e6799f0242dc7e473aa1e16396accbbdd65961/IMG_3351.jpeg" filename="IMG_3351.jpeg" filesize="198907" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="it would look much more scared if Carrie were driving the Rugged Prius down there"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>Indian Garden</h1><div><br>The vegetation became much more lush as we approached Indian Garden, which rests along the Garden Creek.  Carrie walked right by a snake, which scared the absolute bejeezus out of Truman.  We think it was probably a garden snake and probably not a rattlesnake.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lYTEzZjdiNi0yOGNkLTRlOTEtYjBlYS1jNGJlNmNiYTM0NmU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--dbdbebcce8592f9885b0056c0a39e6dd8d646f41" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsWVRFelpqZGlOaTB5T0dOa0xUUmxPVEV0WWpCbFlTMWpOR0psTm1OaVlUTTBObVVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--1d2a87fa23ced69fba42ad5903e18c6da57ea36d/IMG_3361.jpeg" filename="IMG_3361.jpeg" filesize="313448" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="so green!"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82ZTk2ZWNmNS01YTY1LTQ2MDItYTdmOC1hNzdhMjI1Yzc1NTU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--77e3843544cf1df6ac596976b4c70e0dd1ef30af" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyWlRrMlpXTm1OUzAxWVRZMUxUUTJNREl0WVRkbU9DMWhOemRoTWpJMVl6YzFOVFVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--62d0a88ba27f840e2a6477b8d6447c9153d491db/IMG_3366.jpg" filename="IMG_3366.jpg" filesize="110310" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="such an adventurer"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jZjkyOTUwMS02ZTJmLTRkNjktOTE1OC0yYmRiZWFlNWJkNTc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--6bfeb5e833d36533b6639621da6cec2c1f3b6653" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqWmpreU9UVXdNUzAyWlRKbUxUUmtOamt0T1RFMU9DMHlZbVJpWldGbE5XSmtOVGNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--64d2fa19bdaba92fc6c6d077796e025a546aca9d/IMG_3375.jpeg" filename="IMG_3375.jpeg" filesize="343253" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie walks ahead unperturbed by the danger around us"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82Y2Y1YmM4My04NWVkLTRhMjUtODA3My1kYTQ2YjU1ODY1YWE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--804dce2ef312afd695ac05ee47555b982aff2218" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyWTJZMVltTTRNeTA0TldWa0xUUmhNalV0T0RBM015MWtZVFEyWWpVMU9EWTFZV0VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--a5b40c1a3e8620fd335a08c84097db84482c4a39/IMG_3378.jpeg" filename="IMG_3378.jpeg" filesize="244289" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="terrifying!"></action-text-attachment><br>We made it after a surprisingly easy hike of about three hours and set up camp.  There was a small pool by the creek to relax in, and Carrie and I made our first ramen noodle backpacking dinner while taking in the scenery.  The noodles were a little bland, but filling -- and much better than the unfortunate tasting chicken rice that we'd also packed but had to eat earlier in the trip.<br><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iY2Q2YTJiYy01ZWRjLTQ4ZGEtYjg4ZS1kNmFmNWFlZDAxNGU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--5fb40c6570ce6faebc5635b8d222bc20c84941a9" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpWTJRMllUSmlZeTAxWldSakxUUTRaR0V0WWpnNFpTMWtObUZtTldGbFpEQXhOR1VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--3d5567e91a8ed5f20655f318a4feff17844a25c7/IMG_3382.jpeg" filename="IMG_3382.jpeg" filesize="176285" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Truman inflates the camping pad"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zYTQzNDAyNC00ZjFlLTRiZjYtODYyMC1kZGI1MzRmNzBjYmE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--3870c4d3c37c608c266a7b72d0995400570cdccb" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6WVRRek5EQXlOQzAwWmpGbExUUmlaall0T0RZeU1DMWtaR0kxTXpSbU56QmpZbUVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--713d0f14225603de7411832f27ca5179fd3312da/IMG_3391.jpeg" filename="IMG_3391.jpeg" filesize="176526" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Carrie stands triumphant"></action-text-attachment><br><br>There's a three-mile roundtrip hike out to Plateau Point, which overlooks the Colorado River and much of the canyon.  Carrie and I decided to race the sun to try to make it out before sunset.  We hiked over pretty quickly and got there with plenty of time.<br><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iOWYyZjJlNi03ZmYxLTQ2NmUtYmY0ZC05YjZkMGY3Y2I2YjY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--606d6ed9fbba5ba889a9568f3c7bad398d5ea4a4" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpT1dZeVpqSmxOaTAzWm1ZeExUUTJObVV0WW1ZMFpDMDVZalprTUdZM1kySTJZallHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--8389c529988a1b553ed7ce8ba2557ebbc6217cd7/IMG_3399.jpeg" filename="IMG_3399.jpeg" filesize="91163" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="surrounding canyon"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zMTdlOTQyZC1mZjQ2LTRhZjgtOWIwYy0yZDYxZmFjNWVhMDg_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--ad0472eb241df4df97679c486cb30107245fc896" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6TVRkbE9UUXlaQzFtWmpRMkxUUmhaamd0T1dJd1l5MHlaRFl4Wm1Gak5XVmhNRGdHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--4216705f6a0d467be908debd0cfb85dda14f99a2/IMG_3400.jpeg" filename="IMG_3400.jpeg" filesize="79778" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="more canyon"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85YjI1NWIwZS02ZWYwLTRlYjUtYWQzMy1kZDM3ZDE3MTgxNGM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--1fefe8c5173e0821d3b47e78bc1b6c9b7c55a4a1" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1WWpJMU5XSXdaUzAyWldZd0xUUmxZalV0WVdRek15MWtaRE0zWkRFM01UZ3hOR01HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--295f8dd9d422aeb54cef4dba70fa5e1cc0b3de59/IMG_3403.jpeg" filename="IMG_3403.jpeg" filesize="132282" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="there's a lot of this canyon stuff"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8yOTlkZTZkYi0xYTEzLTRlY2QtOGMxMi00MTU0OGI0ZDYzNDA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--09f8f17b92f4f3fac7fee33d91484a849b8f39cf" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt5T1Rsa1pUWmtZaTB4WVRFekxUUmxZMlF0T0dNeE1pMDBNVFUwT0dJMFpEWXpOREFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--aaf9a5ce15362b1ad370207155504cf74ebc9fc2/IMG_3423.jpeg" filename="IMG_3423.jpeg" filesize="86621" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="almost done I promise"></action-text-attachment><br><br>The moon was just setting along with the sun -- we actually got to watch the moon set right in front of us in the twilight.  I also found out that I do not know how to shoot night photography, but trust me it looked really cool.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jZDliODAzMi1kOWIzLTQ0NWUtYmE4OS00YTkxNjRiZTM5NWM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--bbea6b5b44111ec961e0eecc26b9ca22bb4fc62b" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqWkRsaU9EQXpNaTFrT1dJekxUUTBOV1V0WW1FNE9TMDBZVGt4TmpSaVpUTTVOV01HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--ce4c8e50a103f41f9f00f72634b11d3b1cc44a63/IMG_3436.jpeg" filename="IMG_3436.jpeg" filesize="148394" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="tiny sliver of a moon, center"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8wZmFmZDE2Ni01ZGFlLTRiNzQtYWQ5Mi04NDQwYmFmNzkxZDQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--0697308f0c6c14bc233e40e165e031a45d7fd2d8" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt3Wm1GbVpERTJOaTAxWkdGbExUUmlOelF0WVdRNU1pMDRORFF3WW1GbU56a3haRFFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--a8ea3c10128dcaddc8740c7cbdf6f691da7cf22a/IMG_3456.jpeg" filename="IMG_3456.jpeg" filesize="145450" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="twilight makes the rocks look much cooler"></action-text-attachment><br><br>A father and daughter from Minnesota were also out on the point, along with a women's hiking group out of Las Vegas.  The hiking group was extremely excited about the outdoors and kept taking pictures much much much too close to the edge of the plateau that we were on -- up on the railing, doing push-ups on the edge of the rocks.  It was fun to watch, but also very scary.  <br><br>The father and daughter planned to stay through the sunset to watch the stars, and so Carrie and I decided to hang out for a while as well.  We had a lot of fun chatting, and the sky was incredible.  The Orionid meteor shower was to peak in a couple of days, and we got a bit of an early show with some spectacular shooting stars.  Carrie and I hiked back in the dark, on the lookout for both snakes and scorpions (another hiker had seen a rattlesnake slithering off about an hour earlier) -- but none showed themselves.  Looking around, we were also able to see the headlamps of other hikers off in the distance, climbing Bright Angel Trail back up toward the rim.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi84YzhmODkwNy1iNWU0LTQzMTAtYTRkNy05YjlkZjZiODI0OTY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--5a0d373bee5a639d43b49388f2d2226b904f27c3" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs0WXpobU9Ea3dOeTFpTldVMExUUXpNVEF0WVRSa055MDVZamxrWmpaaU9ESTBPVFlHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--727a9cacbb1f1ee85091dbdd3a16e7c85e9c86ec/IMG_3446.jpeg" filename="IMG_3446.jpeg" filesize="110678" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Truman, quite relaxed near a thousand foot drop"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div>	Post	fd06713a-3a30-425b-b8c4-4ea15d4c8ae8	2020-10-23 05:42:09.317058	2020-10-23 05:42:10.477514
ef181e7f-2de8-4a1c-9df4-d8f48167c3b6	content	<h1>The Last Trip</h1><div><br>Our last hike out was about four and a half miles with 3000 feet of elevation gain, so it was going to be a bit of a long day.  Carrie has long maintained that hiking up is much nicer than hiking down, which I have come to agree is true.  It's more of a workout, but much easier on the knees, balance, and brain (you don't have to watch where you're walking so as to avoid tumbling grandly down the canyon quite as much).  We wanted to get an earlier start and got up with the sun to make coffee and start hiking before the heat of the day.<br><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8zYmEwY2MxZi1jYmM3LTQzZTYtYTViOS1iMjYxZmEwMjcwZDI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--7d9809851c5db800f6e8cd3eed11e20081d69ceb" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt6WW1Fd1kyTXhaaTFqWW1NM0xUUXpaVFl0WVRWaU9TMWlNall4Wm1Fd01qY3daRElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--5c9162a2d70ffe32108e7565b60f8577302dd201/IMG_7645.jpeg" filename="IMG_7645.jpeg" filesize="191874" width="640" height="853" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="making oats"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lODdjYjZkYy1jMjMxLTRhMjctOTMwNy02YjQ4YmFhOTkwYzI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--7088178c45e1937cde6fb7ba31bf02fcc343da97" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsT0RkallqWmtZeTFqTWpNeExUUmhNamN0T1RNd055MDJZalE0WW1GaE9Ua3dZeklHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--d7597b0dcf2cf23803344d0f809a5780ef08b532/IMG_3475.jpg" filename="IMG_3475.jpg" filesize="112675" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="enjoying coffee"></action-text-attachment><br><br>The view from our campsite was awesome, and we were sad to leave Indian Garden.  On the way out is a sign admonishing folks to stay on the path.  Fortunately Carrie knew where to go.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9hMjM3OTZhMS00YjViLTRmZTktOWZkYS1kYzEyNTlkZTk0Yzc_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--aef43eaa41d1fdce86ee7c2628da69d9f7ae49a6" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxoTWpNM09UWmhNUzAwWWpWaUxUUm1aVGt0T1daa1lTMWtZekV5TlRsa1pUazBZemNHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--56f8fb7e54f4a1739b08a8a815566686b1f42394/IMG_6129.jpg" filename="IMG_6129.jpg" filesize="141451" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="big rocks all around, best enjoyed with coffee"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8wZDExNzI0Yi1lM2ExLTRiYmUtYTg2Zi0xYjA5MTZiN2MzZTI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--750e2f205b0209bc546bfdc8e2256e19b07c2f84" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt3WkRFeE56STBZaTFsTTJFeExUUmlZbVV0WVRnMlppMHhZakE1TVRaaU4yTXpaVElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--d7035b551a8742eff109b8dfe6e58deb4ac7e18c/IMG_6314.jpeg" filename="IMG_6314.jpeg" filesize="125962" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="a pithy sign"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi80ZGE1OTlkOC1mNjdiLTRiMmYtYWJkZS1kNDdmYzcxOTYxMTg_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--ca771db231d743aa5ec72b4b98db6efb0abc3d4f" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWswWkdFMU9UbGtPQzFtTmpkaUxUUmlNbVl0WVdKa1pTMWtORGRtWXpjeE9UWXhNVGdHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--571685236b49294bca5a86f13811f6809cb1490b/IMG_4469.jpeg" filename="IMG_4469.jpeg" filesize="168221" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="see?  that way."></action-text-attachment><br><br>Fortunately most of the hike up was shaded.  It was pretty tiring, but we took breaks every hour and generally felt okay.  Lots of water, chocolate, meat sticks, fizzing electrolyte tabs, and more water were helpful.  We also got caught behind a mule train with sightseers that stopped every half mile or so to explain what we were looking at (rocks), so we had more opportunities to take a breather and drink some water.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi81MDVhZmU5Yy02ZjQ1LTQ5NGItYTRhYS1hYWQ2ZTZhZTQ1YzA_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--781fc4b5c03f5fb246c44d3e82092ee905aa58f8" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsxTURWaFptVTVZeTAyWmpRMUxUUTVOR0l0WVRSaFlTMWhZV1EyWlRaaFpUUTFZekFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--cb60758afd13409eb4d252201d71f31f5d069687/IMG_9882.jpeg" filename="IMG_9882.jpeg" filesize="126706" width="640" height="360" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="(rocks)"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9kMGIwZjYzZC01ZGRkLTQ4OTYtYTQyZC0yN2FmMWM5NWZiMmU_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--e766254c01574953bdae7473957c37e341c2a7c9" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxrTUdJd1pqWXpaQzAxWkdSa0xUUTRPVFl0WVRReVpDMHlOMkZtTVdNNU5XWmlNbVVHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--ed2204ef2a94b1016065c10c035c25c25d150d56/IMG_4844.jpeg" filename="IMG_4844.jpeg" filesize="87235" width="640" height="360" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="it was still pretty hot"></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi82Nzg3MjRiZC02M2ZmLTRhNWQtOGY5NS05ZTkzYzFmMGI3MGE_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--9607ed5c049a459f3f786c1b4e440d4404bc419d" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsyTnpnM01qUmlaQzAyTTJabUxUUmhOV1F0T0dZNU5TMDVaVGt6WXpGbU1HSTNNR0VHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--1bb75e787218483e04e12276be1908ccf202086f/IMG_4381.jpeg" filename="IMG_4381.jpeg" filesize="90689" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="Truman and Carrie share a last kiss before their bodies fail them and they tumble into the canyon"></action-text-attachment></div><div><br></div><h1>Out</h1><div><br>We made it back to the top of the south rim after about four hours, very tired, but very happy.  Our first stop was the food truck where we inhaled a couple of hotdogs and a late-breakfast burrito that the food truck folks tossed in for free (this was our prize for finishing the hike).  We'd gotten a room at the nearby Bright Angel Lodge and relaxed for a while before putting our name in at the El Tovar dining room.<br><br>El Tovar is the fancy establishment of the canyon, and has a white-tablecloth dinner service which feels very old-school fancy.  We ate famous french onion soup (recommended by president Obama to the British Prime Minister), caesar salad, and filet mignon.  All-in-all it was a wonderful day and an incredible trip.<br><br></div><h1>Thank You</h1><div><br>I wanted to pause here and say thank you again to everyone who so kindly helped Carrie and I make the trip possible with wonderful backpacking-related gifts.  It would not have been possible without your support, and we're deeply grateful to have been able to experience walking through the Canyon.  I don't have the words to describe what the trip felt like, nor for our gratitude.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9lZWU0NDkzMy0yNTc4LTRjMzktYmY4MS04NTI1ODM3ZmFiMWI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--2e3669a280097d432786e1ad06025be01145c9f0" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxsWldVME5Ea3pNeTB5TlRjNExUUmpNemt0WW1ZNE1TMDROVEkxT0RNM1ptRmlNV0lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c18d29c73a00307fe1ea70aa1f2989186f6eb713/IMG_6879.jpeg" filename="IMG_6879.jpeg" filesize="101634" width="640" height="360" presentation="gallery" caption="Truman (very tired) and Carrie (very happy)"></action-text-attachment></div>	Post	0d46a7ab-2b36-46a9-8c7d-c826ec335663	2020-10-23 06:03:15.729763	2020-10-23 06:03:46.38034
b2e2ab0e-7c4b-4f22-8302-ff106257a6e0	content	<div>We are loving your photos and journal! Gretchen and I are thinking that we might need to schedule a trip to the Grand Canyon! This has been one heck of a trip for you both and you have created wonderful memories. Safe travels home!</div>	Thought	121f78ca-0887-4597-99cc-a2cebede9679	2020-10-23 16:08:25.0775	2020-10-23 16:08:25.0775
f438fd81-47ab-442a-be6a-4eeac8c188fd	content	<div>What an awesome trip so far, and I've read every word and looked over every picture.  I can't wait for the next installments!  And to think, we have great wedding day photos to see as well.  Hope both of you are doing fine.  Jefferson and I returned early, happy and with knowing much more about each other, ourselves, and what we want with camping.</div>	Thought	aa19e5d0-d8b3-4b5c-baeb-244406220f09	2020-10-23 20:52:09.246552	2020-10-23 20:52:09.246552
43a1a759-3903-445d-be92-bf338c1b0c4b	content	<h1>The Graaaaaaaand Canyon</h1><div><br>I forgot to mention that, during our Grand Canyon backpacking, Carrie would stop and look around and proclaim (loudly) "it's the Graaaaaaaaand Canyon."  On our way back up the Bright Angel trail we met a family while waiting on some mules to pass; they had two girls maybe eight and ten.  The eight year old exclaimed, twice, "it's the Graaaaaaaaand Canyon" in almost the exact same voice.  Don't ever say we've lost our childlike sense of wonder.<br><br>Carrie also got up early on the day following to take some sunrise shots before we left.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi81ZDc2MWFhZS1hNTM5LTQwMmEtOTQ5Zi0wZWRiOGM3NjRiNTk_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d9525b281999abfbf274745dee86908aa03042f2" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWsxWkRjMk1XRmhaUzFoTlRNNUxUUXdNbUV0T1RRNVppMHdaV1JpT0dNM05qUmlOVGtHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--c85fe6b00ee049229a1a25a0a5b5ed78a9e3fa33/IMG_3531.jpeg" filename="IMG_3531.jpeg" filesize="75637" width="640" height="360" presentation="gallery" caption="The morning light is beautiful in the Graaaaaaaaand Canyon"></action-text-attachment><br><br>The Rugged Prius™ also had its first spot of trouble and wouldn't start just as we were trying to get back on the road.  Carrie left to see about getting a jump -- the car was starting but the engine wasn't -- when I finally thought to try holding the remote key fob thing right up to the ignition button.  Turns out that the car was fine, but the battery in our key was dying.  With that we were on our way (to a battery store in Flagstaff) and then on our way (to Albuquerque).<br><br></div><h1>Albuquerque</h1><div><br>It seems that lots of Albuquerque-ians prefer the ABQ abbreviation and I think it's because the city's name is a nightmare to spell.  Anyway, in ABQ we had the pleasure of staying in another cute Airstream -- this one called Ernest -- at a place called <a href="https://www.stickyfingers-abq.com/">Sticky Fingers</a>.  Alex (chef and art gallery curator) and Michael run the bed and breakfast, as well as a one-table private restaurant -- which is actually a members-only club with members-only restaurant for zoning purposes.  Membership is one dollar per day.<br> <br>This was the single best meal (dinner) followed by the second best meal (breakfast the next day) that we had on the entire trip.  Alex and Michael went out of their way to make the occasion special and prepared a beautiful broth fondue dinner for us.  They also sell a variety of their food products, which Carrie and I bought to take with us on our trip.  I cannot praise this place enough and we'll definitely be staying there the next day.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9iZjE2YTE3Mi1mNTM2LTQxMmUtODBkNi0yZDM4ZDhjOWZkZWQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--6f6596d3d03b926cae204dc5f467d3360fd50510" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxpWmpFMllURTNNaTFtTlRNMkxUUXhNbVV0T0RCa05pMHlaRE00WkRoak9XWmtaV1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--41e76750cee02e6510e2258beb31076f71ad97c9/IMG_3535.jpeg" filename="IMG_3535.jpeg" filesize="129454" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="Dinner is on their patio by their koi pond.  Also we got to meet their cat (Chester) and dog (Ines)"></action-text-attachment><br><br>This was a wonderful day capped by great hosts and a truly wonderful meal.</div>	Post	af1c9dc9-72d0-478e-8f1f-b2f9781bc5b7	2020-10-27 03:48:01.35717	2020-10-27 03:48:01.375871
bae9596e-5178-4462-afe8-14c3948b9381	content	<h1>Leaving Albuquerque</h1><div><br>We wrapped up our stay at <a href="https://www.stickyfingers-abq.com/">Sticky Fingers</a> after a sound night of sleep with a delicious brunch of blueberry beer bread and eggs.  The Airstream also has an eight-track player, so we listened to the "top 20 songs" of the eight-track era.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9kOThmMWRiYi0wZWNhLTRkOTEtYmIyMi0wMzlmNjlhMmIxNDI_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--d00d6118f5960d04b510fa6ab024c477e7e54134" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxrT1RobU1XUmlZaTB3WldOaExUUmtPVEV0WW1JeU1pMHdNemxtTmpsaE1tSXhORElHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--817a2db1cb2c464f453a1bb99d67c2f02cf79e0b/IMG_0717.jpeg" filename="IMG_0717.jpeg" filesize="166280" width="640" height="853" presentation="gallery" caption="So crackly sounding!"></action-text-attachment><br>They also had decor that felt oddly familiar...<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85M2JmMDdlMy0xNTBlLTRhNDktOGVkNS00OWExZGE4ZmMyMWY_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--0f4415bf0e1af654f23354a8d570a67113f33f35" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1TTJKbU1EZGxNeTB4TlRCbExUUmhORGt0T0dWa05TMDBPV0V4WkdFNFptTXlNV1lHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--0ccc0d9edf8249fec882585419de009d70cae372/IMG_3541.jpeg" filename="IMG_3541.jpeg" filesize="65937" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="I can't quite..."></action-text-attachment><br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85YjFhY2YzOS00YTljLTQ0MmMtYmE3Ni1lNGFkZjIxNjlmMGQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--11fde48a9d802e65180bfe726c355fcce0936984" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1WWpGaFkyWXpPUzAwWVRsakxUUTBNbU10WW1FM05pMWxOR0ZrWmpJeE5qbG1NR1FHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--0bdd541a4d0f707af905aaeccfc9370c4c48e190/IMG_3539.jpeg" filename="IMG_3539.jpeg" filesize="88159" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="...put my finger on it."></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Oklahoma City</h1><div><br>Apparently Oklahoma City is going through somewhat of a food renaissance.  We were only able to snag dinner from <a href="http://cheeverscafe.com/">Cheevers</a>, which was good although quite rich.  Our salad, roasted chicken &amp; pepperjack strudel (!), and chicken fried steak (!!) is really the meal I wanted after backpacking, but it was still good two nights on.<br><br>Carrie and I were ready to be home.  I posted about the Graaaaaaand Canyon later that night and we hit the hay.  It would be fun to head back to spend the weekend in OKC -- apparently the coffee there is pretty good, too.</div>	Post	0bca829e-cc43-4cf6-b222-51258ee71605	2020-10-27 03:54:51.841938	2020-10-27 03:54:51.947853
1c69401a-80e9-47f6-95c4-4aa3780553bb	content	<h1>Joplin, MO</h1><div><br>Our first trip through Joplin, MO, saw us making a quick stop for Carrie's first Hardee's dinner.  On our way back through we thought we'd try the jewel of Joplin, <a href="https://fredandredschili.com/">Fred &amp; Red Chili</a>.  Folks rave about their "Spaghetti Red," but we wanted to get back on the road -- I (driving) got a cheeseburger and fries.  Carrie figured she'd better try the chili and ordered a chili cheeseburger.  We figured it'd be garnished with chili, but Fred &amp; Red does not skimp.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi9jYzY1MWM1Yy1jNWZiLTQ1MDEtYjMyYS1jYWY3ODcxYzFiZDQ_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--dd093e52589c05007fd4354b01a5c2334816327d" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWxqWXpZMU1XTTFZeTFqTldaaUxUUTFNREV0WWpNeVlTMWpZV1kzT0RjeFl6RmlaRFFHT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--87f899682ecb7aa55feffad0cecf82b713471022/IMG_3543.jpeg" filename="IMG_3543.jpeg" filesize="120025" width="640" height="480" presentation="gallery" caption="The grand lake chili burger"></action-text-attachment><br><br>It was pretty good, extremely-meat chili.  The burger was pretty good too.<br><br></div><h1>Almost To St. Louis</h1><div><br>Growing up in nearby (-ish) Columbia, MO, I'd spent a fair amount of time visiting Lee Ann and her husband Bob and their three sons, Bobby, Logan, and Lucas, at their home outside of St. Louis.  Lee Ann and Bob went to school with both of my parents at Rockhurst University (then College) in Kansas City, MO, and they've been great family friends since.<br><br>Lee Ann graciously offered to put us up, but Chicago's travel restrictions meant we'd have to stay at a no-contact bed and breakfast in order to ward off a fourteen day quarantine once we returned home.  Instead, Lee Ann and Bob hosted us for a lovely dinner of St. Louis BBQ outside on their front drive.  They were incredibly kind to have us; we had a great time and it was wonderful to see them and talk.  I hadn't been back to their house since probably before high-school -- but I have memories of their swimming lake nearby, of lighting what must have been a 50' roll of firecrackers for the Fourth of July one year, of driving a go-kart around their subdivision, and of taking turns playing computer games with Bobby, Logan, and Lucas.  Lee Ann also had some pictures of tiny-baby Truman.  It's nice to be reminded just how cute I once was.<br><br></div><h1>St. Louis</h1><div><br>Carrie and I stayed at a well-appointed vacation rental via SF Shannon.  We were mostly in-and-out since the next day would bring us home to Chicago.</div><div><br><br></div>	Post	a770b156-02bb-44c0-8f37-2aca0487da8f	2020-10-27 04:11:08.765018	2020-10-27 04:11:08.829457
d8dccf4e-276e-42f1-8b0d-deafca137043	content	<h1>After Returning Home</h1><div><br>I pulled out our candy-and-sweet-things basket in order to stow the remainder of our trip snacks while unpacking and you'll never guess what I saw, quietly tucked into the bottom:  one bag of chocolate covered pretzels that I'd stashed and forgotten I'd placed there before our trip.<br><br>Sorry Tess.</div>	Post	7881a2e0-6ba2-4249-a165-4120ba2ab7b3	2020-10-27 04:28:30.610742	2020-10-27 04:28:30.610742
2fb0f00f-e54c-4491-9735-06d857681ae6	content	<h1>Almost Home</h1><div><br>On our way back through Illinois Carrie and I stopped to stretch our legs (and eat leftover BBQ sandwiches -- thanks again Lee Ann &amp; Bob!) at the Midewin Tallgrass Prairie.  They have lots of grasses, and even a few bison (which we got to see!).  It was a nice stop, but I was ready to be home.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi8yOTdkMGZlZC1jYTc2LTQ5MTEtOTVhMS04YTc5MzgwNjQwMDM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--04d25166d6eee58d736cda3985fbc571bd6f9b4b" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWt5T1Rka01HWmxaQzFqWVRjMkxUUTVNVEV0T1RWaE1TMDRZVGM1TXpnd05qUXdNRE1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--9fb4597d94d8a7500c675165d6bc318226145793/IMG_3545.jpeg" filename="IMG_3545.jpeg" filesize="144378" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="see?"></action-text-attachment><br><br></div><h1>Home</h1><div><br>We arrived back in Chicago around 4pm on Saturday, October 24th.  Carrie is already planning at least our next two backpacking trips, but I was quite ready to unpack, pet our small orange cat gremlin, and relax.  And that's about what I did until now, Monday evening, when I'm finally getting around to back-writing the remaining journal posts.  We also did some photo organization and will be posting that album soon!<br><br></div><h1>Final Stats</h1><div><br><strong>Animals Spotted<br></strong>Snakes:  1<br>Bears:  1<br>Horses (wild):  3<br>Horses (wild only in their hearts):  many<br>Cows:  a ton<br>Long-horned cows:  a ton (by weight)<br>Prairie Dogs:  some, but not enough<br>Elk:  6-10<br>Bighorn Sheep:  4<br>Chipmunks (gold-bellied and otherwise): 10+<br>Ringtailed Cat:  1 (eyes and a brief tail glimpse only)<br>Mule Deer:  a bunch <br>Burrows:  many trail-worthy (+2 amorously calling in Death Valley)<br>Birds (all shapes, but mostly Ravens):  too many<br>Scorpions:  0 (but they were out there, watching)<br><br><strong>Natural Features</strong><br>Trees:  at least one<br>Rocks (large and small):  50+<br>Desolate Texas-panhandled plain:  endless<br><br><strong>Other</strong><br>500 Miles call-and-response "da duh lah da"s:  10+<br>Jay O'Callahan "Oh I did it oh I did it" ditties:  each time we accomplished something after listening to Little Dragon<br><br></div><h1>That's it</h1><div><br>Thank you for your support.  Thank you for helping make our trip possible.  Thank you for all of the kind and funny words that you sent along.  Thank you for your time and for your attention following our journal.  This was an incredible, astounding trip for Carrie and for me; we would not be where we are, or who we are, without you.  Thank you.<br><br>Love,<br><br>Truman (and Carrie)</div>	Post	140951b7-d19d-4514-b8a8-9e0b7e244e57	2020-10-27 04:25:56.511293	2020-10-27 23:14:12.079787
82d30ae5-70f3-4214-9a3a-1b1a55fb35b7	content	<div>Congratulations Carrie and Truman! So happy for you and know that this is just the beginning of a wonderful life together. Sending lots of Love</div>	Thought	44820024-488c-4ab7-82c0-5aecb6ee36d8	2020-10-28 18:07:21.952139	2020-10-28 18:07:21.952139
7dc64c84-8781-4319-b6e9-b8721fa486d2	content	<div>HAY GUYS, CONGRADULATIONS!!! as you start your lives as Mr and Mrs and children, ( To come later ) lol<br><br></div>	Thought	108b6ed6-16f9-463e-b546-caa33e6c392d	2020-10-29 04:27:25.235691	2020-10-29 04:27:25.235691
